title: seven up cake
directions: Combine all ingredients putting seven up in last.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Note:
Save some of crumb mixture for top.

title: chew bread
directions: Butter pan well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix the cake mix with the pie filling (do not add water).
Bake mixture in 9 x 13 dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Cut into 12 equal pieces.
Each piece is 2 points.

title: quick krimmel pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add in sugar while beating, then add baking powder and vanilla.
Beat well on slow speed and fold in crumbs and nuts.
Press out into greased pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream, Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: craig's stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells and let cool.
Finely dice onion and pepper. Brown hamburger and sausage in frying pan while sauteing onion and pepper at same time.
Drain grease from hamburger and sausage, onion, and peppers.
In mixing bowl combine Ricotta cheese with hamburger, sausage, onions, and peppers.
Mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste to the mixture.
Stuff large shells to capacity with mixture.
Add 1/4 inch sauce to cover bottom of casserole dish.
Place shells side by side, filling dish.
Cover shells with light coating of red sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove dish and cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake uncovered for 10 minutes, let cool for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add all other ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: dora's chicken pie casserole
directions: Combine all soups, chicken, peas, carrots, broth and cream. Pour mixture in a "large" casserole dish.
Tear biscuits in half and cover top of casserole.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli in 1 cup water with bouillon cubes.
Bring to a very low boil; reduce heat to medium-low and cook about 7 minutes or until broccoli is tender.
Put milk, cheese cubes and flour in a blender.
Process on medium speed.
Add milk mixture to cooked broccoli mixture.
Add cream.
Cook, stirring frequently, over medium heat until mixture is thickened.
Reduce heat.
Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Add sugar gradually to creamed butter.
Beat in eggs and jam. Alternate flour, allspice with buttermilk.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Bake in well greased pan at 300° for about 40 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Cook bacon; drain and chop up.
Saute onion in bacon fat; drain.
Combine eggs, milk, cream cheese, bacon and seasonings. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
If you like, add more cheese, mushrooms, crab meat or vegetables.
Makes 1 pie.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue-sauce kabobs
directions: Preheat broiler.
In a bowl, combine catsup, brown sugar, lemon juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Brush zucchini pieces lightly with cooking oil.
On 4 long skewers, alternately thread beef, potatoes and zucchini.
Brush with catsup mixture. Broil the kabobs 4 to 5-inches from heat for about 20 minutes. Turn once and brush occasionally with sauce.
Serve kabobs on rice.
(Can be cooked on grill.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: noodles with mushrooms
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients for 6 minutes.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Add noodles.
Cook until all ingredients are absorbed, about 7 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 as a side dish.

title: date fingers
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, beaten egg and dates in a boiler. Cook over low heat, stirring often, until thick.
Cool, then pour date mixture over Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Stir to mix well.
Take small amounts and roll between hands to form finger shapes.
Roll fingers in Angel Flake coconut.
Yields approximately 1 dozen.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix meal, flour, sugar, eggs and buttermilk thoroughly.
Add melted shortening.
Pour into loaf pan to within 1-inch of top. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: buffalo style hot wings
directions: Brown and drain meat; add onion.
Spread half of the potatoes and carrots in a baking dish and cover with half of the meat and onion mixture.
Season to taste.
Cover with half of a can of condensed tomato soup.
Layer remaining ingredients in same order, topping with remaining half can of soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal crackers
directions: Stir sugar, salt, 1 1/2 cups of water and oil together.
Add oats and flour with more water if necessary to make a moist dough. Roll very thin on Pammed cookie sheets.
Cut into squares and prick with a fork.
Bake until light brown in a 300° oven.
Watch carefully as crackers around the edges will brown first.
Remove these as they brown.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In water, put beef, carrots, parsley, celery, onion and bay leaf and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours. Remove beef and carrots and strain. Combine remaining ingredients. Cook, covered, for 45 minutes. Cut up beef in small pieces. Makes 3 1/2 quarts of soup.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening, butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
In another bowl, sift the flour and baking powder.
Add the flour in small batches to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk, beginning and ending with the flour.

title: sugar free coconut pie
directions: Cook pudding by directions.
Then add extracts and 1/2 of the coconut.
Cool and top with Cool Whip and the rest of the coconut.

title: wonderful chicken casserole
directions: Pick cooked chicken from bone in large chunks; place in pan. Mix the sour cream and soup together; pour over chicken.
Cook stuffing according to directions, using chicken broth in place of water.
Drop over chicken mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Stir together and serve.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks.
Cream oleo and shortening together. Combine both mixtures.
Mix buttermilk and soda; add alternately with flour.
Beat slowly; add coconut and pecans.
Fold in well beaten egg whites with sugar added to egg whites; add vanilla.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, stir together the flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
In another bowl, cream the sugar, oil and eggs. Stir in carrots, then add this mixture to the dry ingredients.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) round pans or in a 9 x 13 pan.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Spread refried beans in shallow dish.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread over beans.
Top with cheese, tomatoes and black olives.
Use tortilla chips for dipping.

title: golden sausage egg rolls
directions: Cook sausage over medium-high heat in large skillet, stirring frequently until no longer pink.
Remove from heat and add the cole slaw mix, ginger, garlic, pepper and salt; mix well. Transfer to colander to drain; cool 15 minutes.
Assemble egg rolls as directed on wrapper package, using 1/3 cup sausage mix for each roll.
To cook in a wok, Dutch oven or fryer, add oil to 3-inches deep and heat to 375°.
Fry 4 at a time for 3 minutes or until golden; drain on paper towels.
Serve with your favorite dipping sauce.
Yields 18 to 20 appetizers.

title: savory bran muffins
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together all-purpose flour, whole bran cereal, Parmesan cheese, snipped chives, baking powder, salt and Italian seasoning.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
In a small mixing bowl, combine egg, skim milk and cooking oil.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick coating.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan; serve warm.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and let sit and cool.
Cut lengthwise and hollow out with a spoon.
Set shells aside.

title: fruit cake
directions: Boil sugar, water, raisins and carrots for 5 minutes.
Add cloves, cinnamon, shortening, soda, flour and fruits.
You may vary the amount of citron to your taste.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: velveeta cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and put in crock-pot on low.
Brown meat.
Add meat and salsa to cheese.
When melted, serve with tostito chips.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream margarine, white sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix these together and add corn flakes and coconut.
Bake in 350° oven for about 14 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean and slice strawberries; sprinkle sugar on top and let set for 1 hour. Drain strawberries and fold into Cool Whip. Put in baked pie crust. Put pie in freezer for 10 to 15 minutes to set. Then refrigerate and serve. Serves 8.

title: tomatillo salsa
directions: Combine diced tomatillos, sweet red pepper, yellow pepper and onion in a large glass bowl.
Stir well. Add vinegar, sugar and juices; stir well to combine.
Stir in cilantro, cumin and red pepper. Stir well again to combine. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve salsa with unsalted tortilla chips, beef, pork or chicken.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: almond roca
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and chopped, untoasted almonds.
Stir mixture occasionally with a wooden spoon over medium to medium-low heat.
Cook until candy thermometer reads 280°.
Quickly remove from heat.
Pour into ungreased jelly roll pan and spread out evenly with knife.
While still hot, sprinkle chocolate chips, wait a bit and spread when melted. Sprinkle toasted almonds over top.
Let cool several hours.
Break into small pieces.

title: braised chicken breasts with mustard sauce
directions: Remove
skin
from chicken breasts.
Place on a rack in an electric
frying pan or in frying pan on top of stove.
Add 1 cup water
to
frying
pan.
Cover
and
cook on high until breasts are
almost
done.
Remove
breasts
from frying pan. Heat
grill. Place
breasts on very hot grill for 10 minutes. Turn often and baste with honey/lemon mixture.
Place on a bed of wild rice and top with 3 tablespoons of Mustard Sauce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Melt butter; add bread cubes and onion and brown lightly. Then combine all ingredients and spoon into a casserole dish. Sprinkle fine bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy garlic pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on pan. Smear 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of minced garlic on each pork chop. Cover each pork chop with a thin
layer of cheese, then sprinkle Mrs. Dash. Broil pork chops until cooked, but be sure to frequently check to ensure moist pork chops.

title: pork sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Form sausage into 12 patties; brown on both sides. Cook noodles in boiling water as directed on package. Drain and mix with 2 tablespoons pork fat. Spoon the noodles into buttered 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch rectangular dish. Mix sauerkraut with brown sugar and celery seed. Place on top of noodles. Place sausage on top. Pour beef broth over all and sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs. Place, uncovered, on rack in large electric skillet preheated to 400°. Bake for 1 hour. Have skillet covered and vents closed. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Set aside 1 tablespoon drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
In same skillet, brown sausage; drain off fat.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Spread reserved bacon drippings in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place sausage pieces in dish; sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Pour batter over all.
Bake uncovered at 400° until set, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and gradually add sour cream.
Beat with mixer until creamy, then add taco mix.
Spread mixture in a glass pan.
Top with lettuce, cheese, peppers, onions, olives and tomatoes.
Serve with Doritos chips.

title: honey bites
directions: Combine honey and peanut butter with dry milk powder; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Yields 36 candies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Heat beef and onion until meat turns color, but do not brown it. Drain. Pour meat and onion mixture into a shallow casserole dish. Pour undiluted soup over mixture. Place Tater Tots on top and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 359° until it bubbles. Serves 12. Preparation time: 20 minutes.

title: funshine fizz
directions: Mix orange juice, pineapple juice, club soda and orange sherbet
in blender.
Blend on low speed until mixed completely. Makes
a
good
summertime	treat,	or
good for birthday parties!

title: low cholesterol apple-oat bran muffins
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Add apples.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into muffin pan that has been sprayed with Pam coating.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
124 calories.

title: harvest pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops in butter.
Remove and set aside.
Cook apples and onions in skillet drippings until onion is tender.
Stir in cider, water, brown sugar, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Return pork to skillet and simmer, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes, until pork chops are tender.
Combine cornstarch and apple cider; stir into hot liquid.
Cook until mixture thickens. Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: phyllis' corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove bacon; leave 3 tablespoons of grease in pan.
Add onion; cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and a dash of pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serves 6.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together 1 egg, melted butter and cake mix.
Pat this mixture down in a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: apple pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture. Mix well and fold in apples, vanilla and nuts.
Top with coconut. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: sliced frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Put 1/4 cup juice and marshmallows in medium saucepan.
Heat on low heat until marshmallows melt.
In large mixing bowl, soften cream cheese with a little whipping cream. Whip the remaining cream.
Add salt and melted marshmallows to the cream mixture.
Fold in whipped cream and fruit.
Spoon into four (No. 2) cans.
Cover with foil and freeze.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Make meat balls; cook in large pot with sauce.

title: reuben-kraut casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut and mix with onions and sour cream.
Spread the mixture in the bottom of a 9 X 13 pan.	Evenly distribute the corned beef and Mozzarella cheese over the top.
Top with broken bite-sized bits of rye bread.
Drizzle the entire dish with melted butter and bake in a 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon herb baste for cornish hens
directions: Brush mixture on hens while grilling for a delicious lemon flavor.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and garlic; cool.
Add Mozzarella cheese, bread crumbs, parsley, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon enough sauce to cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stuff cooked shells and place in pan.
Cover with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.

title: glazed meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt and eggs; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
In a large skillet, brown meatballs in oil, turning occasionally.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to coat meatballs with glaze.
Serve warm in chafing dish.
Makes 48 meatballs.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda in mixing bowl.
Bring to a boil the shortening, butter and cola.
Remove from heat and pour over dry ingredients.
Add eggs and buttermilk; beat well. Stir in marshmallows and vanilla. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: scallops and bacon
directions: Cook scallops in margarine for 5 minutes.
Cut bacon into 2-inch pieces.
Arrange bacon and scallops alternately on skewer. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
To bake, insert skewers in uncooked potato halves, so they will stand upright.
Bake at 475° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Slice sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Pre-boil potatoes, carrots and onion.
Mix brown gravy by package directions.
Mix all ingredients and bake in casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, remove stems and chop enough to make 1 cup. In a saucepan, cook mushroom stems, onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs and cheese.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Arrange caps in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: tomato and basil rice
directions: Heat olive oil and saute onion until translucent.
Add tomatoes and water.
Bring to a boil and add salt, pepper, garlic powder and basil.
Bring to a second boil and add rice and stir.
Reduce to low heat and cover.
Cook until liquid is absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Using fork, break up tuna and place half of it in bottom of medium-size casserole dish.
Pour half of the soup over it and cover with half of crackers, which have been finely crushed. Repeat with rest of ingredients.
Dot with margarine, if desired. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange wild rice with raisins and apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, combine cooked rices. Gently toss together raisins, almonds, parsley, zest, apple, oil, orange juice, salt and pepper with combined rices.
Place mixture in casserole.
Cover with foil; heat thoroughly for 20 minutes.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Roll graham crackers (or use a food processor).
Mix with 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture, saving 1 cup for top of pudding.
Cook milk, 1 cup sugar, salt, egg yolks, flour and vanilla until thick.
Pour into lined pan.
Cover with meringue made with the egg whites left from the pudding.
Then cover with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin nut squares
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and pour in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with cake mix.
Drizzle melted butter over top.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: layered salad deluxe
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in order listed in a large salad bowl.
Combine salad dressing, sour cream and dressing mix; mix well.
Spread over top of vegetables, sealing to edge of bowl. Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired. Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss gently before serving.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: In blender, mix all ingredients except pie shell, coconut and chopped nuts.
Blend until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in coconut and pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Place cut up chicken in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix soup, milk, vegetables and onion in saucepan.
Heat until blended and vegetables are slightly cooked.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and pour over cornbread stuffing.
Add 1 cup chicken broth and stir well.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt and milk and bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to 232° or until small amount of mixture forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and drop in oleo and peanut butter.
Cool to lukewarm and add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens.
Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: my french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a screwtop jar.
Shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Empty envelope of gelatin into blender.
Add lemon juice, onion slices and boiling water; cover blender and blend at high speed for 40 seconds.
Add mayonnaise, paprika, dill and salmon. Cover and blend at high speed briefly.
Add cream, 1/3 at a time, and blend after each addition.
Blend 30 seconds longer.
Pour into 4-cup mold which has been lightly coated with salad oil. Chill for at least 4 hours.
Unmold.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion, garlic and squash in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add mushrooms.
Remove. Add sausage and saute; drain and discard remaining grease.
Pour Hunt's in skillet and add all of the ingredients.
Serve over spaghetti and top with Mozzarella cheese.
You may also layer spaghetti, sauce and cheese and bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill for several hours.
Roll dough into small marble size balls. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and roll in powdered sugar.
After real cool, roll them in powdered sugar again.

title: butter glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots until tender; drain.
Over medium heat combine in skillet the butter, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
When bubbly add carrots and parsley.
Remove from heat.
Stir until carrots are coated.
Serve immediately.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Stir ingredients together until lemonade mix is dissolved. Just before serving, add 1 quart of ice cubes and 1 to 2 bottles of sugar-free 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: raisin squares
directions: Cook raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Add butter; let melt, then cool.
Add egg, flour, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, baking soda, allspice, cloves and salt.
Pour into ungreased cookie sheet with edges.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 shortbread
directions: Knead the flour into the softened butter; then knead the granulated sugar into the flour-butter mixture. Press firmly into a well-greased 8-inch square pan or shortbread mold. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° or until a delicate brown. Cut in 36 squares while still hot. Return to oven a few minutes to dry out edges. Let cool in pan or on wire rack.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add sugar slowly.
Continue until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and nuts until blended.
Pour into well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool 2 hours and remove from pan.

title: seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Mix crabmeat, cheese and onions.
Place in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute by hand).
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in saucepan. Bring to boil and boil for 4 minutes. Set aside off heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats; mix. Drop onto cookie sheets to cool.

title: watergate pudding
directions: Mix crushed pineapple and instant pistachio pudding in a bowl. Add Cool Whip and mix well with spoon.
Add nuts, if desired. Decorate with sliced pineapple and cherries.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put pork chops in casserole dish, then add a layer of potatoes and then a layer of onion.
Salt and pepper, then add cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into balls.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or overnight.
Then dip in chocolate.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350-375 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: eggs portugal
directions: Brown sausage (Deans or Owens); drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover bottom with 8 slices of bread, cut in cubes.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese.
Add drained sausage.
Mix eggs (beaten) in milk and mustard and pour over sausage.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, top with can of mushrooms (drained) and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people. Serve with fruit and pastries.

title: savory eggs(christmas brunch)
directions: To yolks, add ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Replace yolk mixture in whites.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: apple fritters(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Beat egg with milk; stir 1 tablespoon melted Crisco with the fruit. Combine dry ingredients. Add to egg mixture and stir. Drop from tablespoon into deep Crisco. Fry about 4 minutes until brown. Serve hot. Makes 16.

title: easy chicken loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pack mixture into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Unmold onto hot platter.
Garnish with parsley and hard-cooked egg segments.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.
Contains 191 calories per serving.

title: faye and hildy's celery seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together, sprinkle with sugar or Sweet 'N Low to taste. Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for at least an hour.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Add milk and crackers, then coconut and vanilla.
Cook until thick.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except dry cake mix, pecans and melted butter.
Line pan with wax paper.
Pour mixture in pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top (dry).
Sprinkle pecans on that.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn upside-down.
Take paper off and let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the flour and soda.
Combine the butter, sugar, vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat in eggs.
Slowly add flour mixture and stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: molded salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water.
Add the cool water.
When cool and jello-like, fold in the remaining ingredients.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mash
sweet
potatoes
and
mix in all the ingredients. Bake until
firm and browned on top.
Then add topping and let cook for 15 minutes on 375°.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup and butter.
Beat together well.
Add oatmeal and coconut, stirring together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This is a rich pie very much like pecan.
Pie is done when filling is set.

title: linzertorte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, butter a 10 inch spring form that is 2 inches high.
Work the flour, hazelnuts, butter, sugar, egg, 1 egg yolk, cinnamon and lemon zest to a dough.
Press 3 quarters of the dough into the bottom and sides of the pan.
Fill with jam.
Roll out the remaining dough 1/4 inch thick, cut into strips, criss-cross them over the filling, brush with 1 egg yolk.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chocolate mint sugar cookie drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in mint chips.
Shape into balls.
Roll in remaining sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend in oleo, flour and nuts and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Combine cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on the baked crust.
Add cold milk to pudding and beat with mixer until thick.
Spread pudding on top of second layer.
Refrigerate.
More Cool Whip can be spread over top when pudding sets.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.

title: low-fat spanish rice
directions: In medium saucepan, over high heat, bring broth to a boil. Add rice, cover and reduce to low setting.
Cook 50 minutes or until rice is tender.
Saute garlic, onion, green pepper and celery in 3 to 4 tablespoons juice from tomatoes in a large skillet over medium-high heat for 5 to 7 minutes or until softened.
Add tomatoes to skillet with remaining juice.
Stir in seasonings and honey and bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 10 minutes.
When rice is tender, stir into tomato mixture.
Heat until hot, approximately 5 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together the cinnamon, salt, soda and flour.
Add to the first mixture. Stir in the rhubarb.
Mix and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle on 3 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and ketchup together with mixer.
Add onion and shrimp.
Blend all ingredients; serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: *You can use bacon (crumbled up), Canadian bacon or ham.

title: french bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; add margarine. Gradually add water to dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes. Stir in enough additional flour to make stiff dough.
Turn on floured board and knead until smooth, 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap or towel; rest 20 minutes.
Divide dough in half. Roll out on lightly floured board to size of 15 x 10-inches; roll up taper ends.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes or leave on skins.
Cut each potato into wedges (4 each).
In mixing bowl, combine oil, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Add cut-up potatoes; toss to coat.
Wrap potatoes in heavy foil.
Seal edges tightly.
Grill packet on medium to hot grill about 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
These can also be cooked in the oven.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix the top ingredients in a bowl and use this mixture in place of your usual milk when making biscuits.
When your biscuits are done, sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: grandma froning's rhubarb pie
directions: Note: Fresh rhubarb is best!
If frozen rhubarb is used, defrost prior to adding to filling.
Canned rhubarb must be drained first and isn't as good.

title: easy chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix together and pat in a pie pan.
Prick with a fork.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: french dressing
directions: Use a blender to mix.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown hamburger, drain grease.
Cook hamburger with the taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with the refried beans.
Layer the hamburger, onion, salsa and cheese over the refried beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix olives and sour cream and top the baked mixture. Serve with nachos.

title: party potatoes
directions: Melt together oleo and cream cheese.
Add soup and onion; mix together until smooth.
Put 1/2 of potatoes in a greased pan and pour on half of the sauce.
Sprinkle the rest of the potatoes and add the remainder of sauce.
Top with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 325°, covered, for 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and roll chicken.
Bake in lightly buttered pan for 1 hour at 350° until brown.

title: edna's punch
directions: Stir sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Add all of the other ingredients except Sprite.
Freeze overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter sides and bottom of pan.
Cook 10x sugar, oleo and evaporated milk.
Stir constantly.
When it starts to boil, boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir and pour in pan.
Cool completely.
Cut and enjoy!

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Melt yeast in warm water.
Add egg, oil, sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Pan out.
Bake in muffin pan at 425°.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook livers, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Stir soup mix, water and hot pepper sauce into skillet.
Heat to boiling; stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Use fork or wire whisk to dissolve cranberry sauce in jello mixture. Add pineapple, undrained.
Stir to blend.
Let jello chill.

title: one-pot sunday dinner
directions: Dust roast with flour and brown.
Put into large Dutch oven and surround it with potatoes, carrots and the green beans.
Slice onions over the top and cover with both cans of the soup, which have been mixed together with 1/2 can of water to blend.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, or until done.

title: hidden hot dogs
directions: Turn oven to 450°.
Open package of rolls and separate the little triangles.
Flatten each triangle a little bit with your hands.
Open hot dogs and wrap each one in a flattened roll. Pinch the dough together on top so that each hot dog stays wrapped.
Put the wrapped hot dogs on a baking pan.
Bake until they puff and are light brown, about 10 minutes.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: In large bowl thoroughly combine first 7 ingredients, then stir in next 4 ingredients.
Add to graham cracker mixture and blend thoroughly.
Pack firmly into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch aluminum foil pan.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 days.
Let stand about 2 hours at room temperature before serving.
Makes 1 (8 ounce) loaf.

title: arctic salad
directions: In a bowl, blend cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Stir in raspberries, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze 8 hours.
To serve, set out 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Serves 12 to 18.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Press into 13 x 10-inch dish.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cool. Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled pretzel mix.
Stir together remaining ingredients; put mixture in the refrigerator to chill for 10 minutes.
Pour over top of dish and refrigerate.
All ingredients can be substituted for low calorie products.

title: oatmeal chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, pour water over oatmeal and allow to stand 10 minutes. Add sugars and butter, stirring until the butter melts.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Sift flour, cocoa, soda and salt together.
Add to batter.
Mix well. Stir in half of the chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top of cake with walnuts and remaining chips. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Lightly butter a large casserole dish.
Cover bottom of dish with broccoli florets. Spread chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and cooking sherry and stir together well.
Pour mixture over chicken and spread out evenly.
Cover sauce with grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Spray pie pan with Pam; line bottom of pan with peppers.
Put grated cheese over the peppers.
Beat eggs and pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until cheese and eggs are firm and will cut in slices.
Great with seafood.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Put in casserole.
Blend 2/3 cup Cheddar cheese, peppers and sour cream.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thick.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Boil sugar and cornstarch with 1-cup water until thick; remove from fire and add blackberry gelatin.
Thaw and drain 4 cups blackberries; fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: brown sugar custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Break eggs into mixture and fold in. Don't beat.
Melt butter and add to milk.
Stir the two mixtures together.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°, then reduce heat to 375° until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add rice, can of broth (and enough water to make 2 cups), 2 tablespoons butter or oleo and onions.
Cook according to rice directions.
Mix with cream of chicken soup; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole.
Top with chicken breasts; salt and pepper chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine Jell-O pudding, egg yolks and milk in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of vanilla wafers on bottom and sides of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add a layer of banana slices and of pudding.
Continue layering wafers, bananas and pudding, ending with pudding.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl; cut in 3/4 cup butter thoroughly with pastry blender until mixture resembles very fine crumbs.
Press mixture evenly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan, using a piece of plastic wrap to press crumb mixture firmly in pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cool 'n easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Mix water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Stir into gelatin until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.
Stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping, if desired.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn, reserving 1/4 cup liquid. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, parsley flakes and paprika. Combine eggs, melted butter and liquid from corn.

Mix well. Add to dry ingredients all at once and stir until smooth. Fold in drained corn. Drop batter from a tablespoon into deep fat heated to 375°. Fry, a few at a time, until golden brown on all sides.
Remove from fat.
Drain on paper towel. Keep hot while frying remaining fritters.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again. Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add taco seasoning and mix well; cool. In large bowl, mix macaroni, green pepper, onions, cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and seasonings; chill.
Just before serving, stir in seasoned meat, French dressing and chips; toss lightly. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: yogurt-grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1-gallon Ziploc bag.
Marinate in bag several hours or overnight in the refrigerator.
Lift from marinade and grill over charcoal grill.
(Based on Iranian cooking with yogurt!)

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pumpkin.
Add pecans. Dot top with oleo.
Bake at 250° for 50 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix margarine, cloves, mashed garlic, salt, celery seed and black pepper together.
Set aside.

title: zucchini dessert
directions: Boil 30 minutes all ingredients together.
Pack in pint jars. Process for 20 minutes in pressure canner.
Yield 6 to 7 pints. Tastes just like real pineapple.

title: chocolate spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 10-inch tube baking pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix flour, soda, cocoa and spices.
Blend in eggs, dry ingredients and applesauce until well mixed.
Fold in raisins, nuts and dates.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: light and lively salad
directions: Mix together with reduced calorie Ranch dressing.

title: almost better than sex cakes
directions: Prepare the cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish according to package directions.
When done, remove from oven and while still hot, poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon. Pour sweetened condensed milk, then caramel topping into holes. Spread entire cake with whipped topping.
Sprinkle crushed candy bars on top of cake.
Refrigerate cake until serving time.
Cake can be frozen.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix crushed crackers and margarine and cover top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put sliced onion in bottom of an empty 3-pound peanut butter jar, then fill with sliced cucumbers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate for 5 days, then eat and enjoy.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and marshmallows in a saucepan.
Cook and stir until sugar and marshmallows melt.
When bubbles cover entire surface, boil and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in butter, salt, chocolate bits and vanilla until chocolate bits are melted.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread into buttered 9 inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 64 squares and enjoy.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook sugar, Karo, milk and peanuts until 240°; remove from fire.
Add remaining ingredients; stir good and spoon out on foil.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: little barbecue wieners
directions: Empty package into a medium sized saucepan. Let simmer in the whole bottle of barbecue sauce. This is a great appetizer.

title: beefy mushroom roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Brown roast in a pot on top of stove in Crisco.
Drain grease; add beefy mushroom soup.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 2 hours (depending on size of roast).
Will have enough for gravy.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature. Mix cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and Accent until blended.
Add 1/2 cup pecans and 1/4 cup parsley.
Shape mixture into ball.
Place in bowl lined with waxed paper.
Chill overnight.

title: marinated onions and cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 6 hours.
Drain.
Mix sugar and vinegar.
Dissolve, then add sour cream.
Mix and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil until clear and thick and bubbling.
Cook for about 5 minutes, then add 2 to 3 cartons of clean, fresh, cold strawberries.
Put in prepared pie crust.
Just before serving, top with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Place sugar, oil and pumpkin in large mixer bowl and beat well at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt together and fold into batter.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Do not open oven door under 1 hour.
Let cool slightly in pan before turning onto cake rack.

title: egg salad
directions: Hard boil eggs; remove 1/2 to 2/3 yolks.
Chop remaining yolks and whites.
Add chopped olives.
Mix in mustard and salad dressing to taste.

title: potato salad
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Boil this, stirring constantly, on low heat until thick.
Chill.
Then add real Kraft mayonnaise dressing.
Mix dressing with sliced, cooked potatoes, 8 boiled chopped eggs, celery and onion.

title: flavored applesauce
directions: Bring to boil 1 1/2 cups applesauce and 3/4 cup water.
Add jello; apricot is great, raspberry is good, too.
Stir well; add pineapple (no need to drain).
Add remaining applesauce.
To keep the sugar content low, I use unsweetened applesauce and sugar-free jello.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Mix all ingredients, set aside.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Drain potatoes and mash well.
Add vanilla, flour, margarine, egg and sugar.
Make small balls and put a marshmallow in center of each ball.
Roll in coconut.
Place on greased baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients. Put in large pan. Melt butter. Mix with potato chips. Spread on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: t.v. snacks
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Pour over cereal and stir.
Cook 2 hours at 200°.

title: pump up your pumpkin
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and whipped topping.
Whip together.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup half and half and add pudding.
Wire whip and let stand 3 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and spices.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Chill 2 hours.
Top with whipped topping and nuts (optional).

title: baked crackers
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over crackers.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion.
Toss with a dressing of remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: baked french donuts
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other mixture alternately with milk.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
While hot, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Makes about 12.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spoon into buttered shallow 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 1 hour).
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender (1 hour).
Cool, deskin, debone and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Set aside.
Saute onions and butter.
Add remaining ingredients except asparagus and almonds.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Add chicken and asparagus. Put into a 3-quart casserole and top with almonds.
Bake at 350° unti bubbly (about 30 minutes).

title: cream cheese cookies(for christmas)
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy. Gradually add sugar and cream cheese making sure mixture is smooth. Beat in egg yolk, vanilla, and flour. Use a cookie press or chill until firm, roll and cut with decorative cutters. Decorate for the holiday. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Yield 3-4 dozen.

title: any flavor slush
directions: Boil water.
Stir in Jell-O and sugar until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and water.
Freeze.
Makes a gallon of frozen slush base.
Scrape and serve with 7-Up.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in an airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup of mix to a cup of boiling water.

title: grandmother's homemade noodles
directions: Bone raw fish and run through food chopper.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk, crumbs and egg.
Mold into loaf and bake, uncovered, in fairly hot oven for 1/2 to 3/4 hour. Serve accompanied with sauce.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Cream butter with 7/8 cup of sugar.
Add well beaten egg, then the milk and vanilla.
Mix the dry ingredients together and add alternately to the milk mixture, beating thoroughly.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Saute the veggies in bacon drippings.
Mix the soup and the milk and evaporated milk together and heat; add the sauteed veggies and heat through; don't boil.
Serve in big soup cups. Makes 3 large soup cups or 4 small ones of chowder.
Crumble bacon atop each as you serve the soup.

title: fruited ice tea
directions: Combine instant tea powder and the cold water; stir until the tea is dissolved.
Add sweetener, orange juice and lime juice. Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve over ice in tall glasses.
Makes 6 servings.
Garnish with orange slices and fresh cranberries.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Mix first six ingredients together and pat one-half of mixture into 9 x 13 pan.
Melt caramels with evaporated milk. Pour over crust.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over caramel mixture and top with remaining crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in 2 c. boiling water.
Add the cherry syrup plus enough cold water to make 1 1/2 c.
Put in the refrigerator to thicken.
When partially set, add the cranberry sauce, cherries, cut in half, and the nuts, apples and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until set.
This keeps well and can be made ahead.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Cook noodles; drain well.
Make layer of noodles, layer of sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/3 of the nuts, layer of spinach, layer of Mozzarella and Parmesan, layer of sauce and layer of noodles.
Repeat.
Top with cheese and nuts.

title: sugarless blueberry muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a small bowl, whisk together the eggs, oil and orange juice and add to the flour mixture.
Before the flour and liquid ingredients are completely combined, fold in the blueberries, stirring gently.
Fill well-greased muffin tin about 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, onion and pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is done.
Add broth and tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nancy's macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Vegetable may be changed to your favorites.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix rice, water, juice and salt just to moisten in pan, then bring to quick boil.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add marshmallows, fruits and nuts.
Cool to room temperature or in fridge.
Fold in the cream.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: To make pizza crust:
Spread rolls on greased jelly roll pan. Bake crust according to package directions.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until veggies are tender, about 1 hour.

title: little grandma's divinity
directions: In a 1 qt. heavy saucepan, combine sugar and corn syrup with 1/2 c. water, over low heat cook stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cover, cook 1 minute or until sugar crystallize on the side of pan melts.
Uncover and bring to boil without stirring. Cook to 238° on candy thermometer or until a small amount in cold water forms a SOFT ball.
Meanwhile in large bowl with an electric mixer at high speed, beat the egg whites with salt until stiff peaks form when beaters are slowly raised.
In a thin stream, pour half of hot syrup over egg whites, beating constantly at high speed, until stiff peaks form.
Continue cooking rest of syrup to 256° on candy thermometer (bringing it to 260° won't hurt), or until a small amount in cold water forms a HARD ball.

title: max's hush puppies
directions: Mix wet ingredients and add to mixed dry ingredients.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Spoon into 375° deep fat oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Remove and serve.
Makes 30 hush puppies.
*Hot peppers chopped into batter makes them good.

title: no peek beef casserole
directions: In crock-pot, put all ingredients except wine.
Mix together well.
Cover and cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.
During last hour of cooking, add wine and stir.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a saucepan, cook mushrooms and green pepper in butter until pepper is tender. Blend in soup. Gradually stir
in milk.
Add chicken and pimento.
Heat, stirring now and then. Serve in patty shells or on toast.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Beat until well blended.
Chill until fairly stiff.
Spread on pumpernickel rounds.

title: six weeks bran muffins
directions: Mix bran cereal, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper and celery in oleo until crisp. Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Add vegetables and chicken; heat through.
Serve with rice.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into
small
pieces.
Add nuts and berries and pour salad dressing over all and mix.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Grate cheese; set aside.
Mix corn bread batter.
Heat greased iron skillet.
Put half batter in skillet, then add browned beef with onions.
Sprinkle cheese on top of this.
Add remaining batter.
Cook approximately 1 hour. Be careful not to let cheese touch sides of skillet or it will stick when turned out.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and let stand until dissolved.
Add about 1/2 the flour.
Beat 5 minutes.
Gradually add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and no longer stretchy (about 10 minutes), adding a small amount of flour as needed.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn over to grease top. Cover with towel and let rise in warm place until double in size. Punch down; let rise again.
Make into 5 or 6 loaves.
Let rise. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
This recipe will serve 40 people.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook meat; mix taco season package in meat.
Mix both cans of chili.
Heat oven to 350°.
First put some chips on bottom of pan. Make sure you mix chili with meat, then put meat with chili on top of chips.
Put more chips on top.

title: texas hash
directions: Lightly brown meat; drain off grease.
Add onion and peppers and cook with meat for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish; cover.
Bake 45 minutes.
Last 15 minutes remove lid and spread desired amount of cheese on top.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted margarine and press lightly into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: bread starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2
cup
warm
water.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Leave at room temperature for 24 hours.
Feed 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potatoes and 1 cup warm water. Leave out 12 hours.
Use 1 cup starter for baking and put 1 cup back in refrigerator.

title: wanda's noodles
directions: Mix together very gently and place in a greased casserole. Sprinkle with grated cheese or cover with spaghetti sauce and meat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together; put into a casserole bowl.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(This will freeze.)

title: slow country boil
directions: Fill pot half full of water.
Add salt to Worcestershire sauce and margarine.
Add sausage; boil 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; boil 5 minutes.
Add onions; boil 5 minutes.
Lift strainer and check potatoes and onions for tenderness.
Add corn; boil 5 minutes.
Add shrimp boil and hot sauce; let come to boil.
Remove vegetables after draining and place in a large container.
Add medium size shrimp (1/2 pound per person); boil 3 minutes.
Remove and serve. This is good for a family gathering.

title: colorful candy popcorn balls
directions: Pour popcorn, peanuts and M&M's into huge bowl.
Mix. Put margarine and marshmallows in large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Using pot, remove bowl.
Mix. Add Jell-O gelatin to marshmallow mixture.
Stir until mixture is same color.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Stir with spoon until popcorn is covered.
Grease hands with margarine.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place on waxed paper until cool.

title: greek herbal chicken
directions: Combine seasonings with butter.
Rub butter seasonings onto chicken.
Bake in slow 300° oven 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter with corn syrup in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add brown sugar and stir to dissolve.
Cook syrup to hard ball stage.
To check, drop some syrup into cup of cold water and when it forms a firm ball it is done.
Takes about 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda, stirring to blend.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat evenly.

title: caramel corn
directions: Blend brown sugar, oleo, salt and Karo together and boil 8 minutes.
Take pan off heat and add baking soda and butter.
Into very large mixing bowl, pour mixture over 6 quarts popped corn. Peanuts or pecans can be added to popped corn.
Mix thoroughly. Bake on 2 cookie sheets at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
M - M - M - M - Good.

title: better baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl cook ziti until just barely tender; drain and place in a large bowl.
Mix the Ricotta and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese with ziti.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover bottom of pan with 1/2 spaghetti sauce.
Spoon the ziti mixture into pan.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and top with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until lightly brown.

title: skillet chicken in golden gravy
directions: Put oil in frypan.
Brown chicken about 10 minutes each side. Take out of pan. Stir onion in and cook until tender.
Blend in soup and water.
Return chicken to pan and spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes or until tender. Serve with noodles.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add sugar.
Add small amount of flour then 1 egg over and over until used up.
Place in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put hamburger, soup mix, crackers and barbecue sauce in mixing bowl.
Beat egg in separate bowl.
Mix together with hands until well mixed.
Put in baking pan.
Put in oven at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes, or until light brown.

title: mrs. bratcher's cream candy
directions: In a heavy deep pan mix sugar and salt.
In a small bowl mix the half and half and baking soda.
Add this to the sugar and salt.
Blend well.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Turn the heat on medium and begin stirring.
Stir constantly until it begins to boil.
You do not stir any more.
Let boil until it reaches hard crack on a candy thermometer, or when dropped in a cup of cold water, it becomes a piece that when tapped on the cup will make an audible sound.
(On my stove this is always 30 minutes.)

title: easy pralines
directions: Mix ingredients in heavy, 2-quart saucepan, then stir and cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Then add pecans and stir and cook to a full, all-over boil.
Then boil slowly about 3 to 5 minutes, stirring often, until candy reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and beat until candy thickens, but still looks shiny.

title: harold's old fashion collard greens
directions: Boil cured ham hocks until tender.
Remove ham hocks from boiler.
Add collard greens to liquid in boiler.
Put ham hocks on top of greens.
Then put bacon drippings in and bring to a boil. Simmer on low heat until tender.
Add a pinch of salt and chopped onion.

title: crab delicious
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add flour and mix well.
Add milk and cook until creamy sauce forms, stirring constantly.
Add seasoning, ketchup and crabmeat.
Cook for 2 minutes. Add egg and cheese and mix well until cheese melts.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, celery, onions and peppers through food chopper. Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add brown sugar, mustard, cinnamon and vinegar.
Mix all together. Mix well and put in jars. Requires no cooking and will keep.
This is a very good relish.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup.
Melt in cream cheese. Stir or beat until smooth. Remove from stove. Add gelatin and remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm, preferably overnight.

title: apple cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in apples (mixture will be thick).
Spread in pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until toothpick stuck in middle of cake cakes out clean.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt.
Makes 10 to 15 servings.

title: china sun pork
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of the juice.
Mix reserved juice with 1/2 cup of water, soy sauce, cornstarch, vinegar and pepper flakes.
Set aside.

title: cold dill peas
directions: Cook and drain peas thoroughly.
Mix together other ingredients very thoroughly.
Carefully combine with peas. Chill and garnish with more dill or chives.

title: blueberry peach coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash berries until blue color is gone. Drain peaches; lay on paper towel.
Set juice aside.
In small bowl, combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine.
Set aside.
Make muffin batter, substituting juice along with liquid for correct amount.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Cut peaches in half.
Press into batter, fat-side up.
Sprinkle berries on top. Add flour/sugar/cinnamon mixture over top.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Dice ham in a medium size bowl; add sour cream a little at a time so you will not get too much. Add chopped cream cheese and picante sauce. Mix ingredients well. Spread on flour tortillas and roll up. You may cut in half or leave whole.

title: my mother's applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add applesauce and beaten egg. Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts and combine the 2 mixtures.
Bake in loaf pans 45 to 60 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Line an 8-inch or 9-inch square pan with foil; butter foil.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan stir together sugar, cocoa and salt; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Boil without stirring to 234° or until syrup, when dropped into cold water, forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
(Bulb of candy thermometer shouldn't rest on bottom of pan.)
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature to 110° (lukewarm).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses some gloss.
Quickly spread into prepared pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 36 pieces; 1 3/4 pounds.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together in saucepan. Add milk, eggs, vanilla and margarine. Cook until thick; have to keep it stirred as you cook. Pour in baked pie shell. Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: pumpernickel dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Cut top off pumpernickel round and carefully hollow out.
Fill round with dip.
Cut up the bread and use to dip.

title: angel biscuits
directions: The above measurements may be cut in half for smaller families.

title: banana split pie
directions: Add 1 stick butter and graham cracker crumbs together; press in bottom of glass pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for several hours before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add package of taco seasoning mix and about half of taco sauce.
Simmer.
Put tortilla chips on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then ground beef mixture.
Layer cheese on meat.
Then add lettuce, onion and tomato.
Mix remaining taco sauce and 1/2 of bottle of Zesty Italian dressing and pour over salad.

title: strawberry icing(strawberries make a good frosting.)
directions: Stem and wash strawberries.
Crush in a medium sized bowl, and stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Let stand until juicy, then gradually add powdered sugar.
Whip until creamy.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Cream cheese, chilies, sour cream, picante sauce and ham together.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll up into a roll. Place in Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator to cool, then cut in pieces and serve.

title: sandies (cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add 2 teaspoons water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in flour and nuts; chill for 4 hours.
Shape into ball or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 325° about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: yams and apples for 50
directions: Combine sugar, 1/2 cup butter, salt and water.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Slice cooked yams 1-inch thick.
Slice apples 1/2-inch thick.
Carefully arrange yams and apples in alternate layers in steam table pan.
Pour over with syrup.
Top with melted butter. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour until apples are tender.
May garnish with coconut.

title: banana cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and a small loaf pan.
Place large marshmallows 2 inches apart in pan.
Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt together.
Add mashed bananas, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add unbeaten egg whites and mix thoroughly.
Stir in chopped nuts. Carefully spoon over marshmallows in greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, according to pans used.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let sit in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Really better made a day ahead.

title: ginger chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet, over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry chicken until no longer pink; remove.
Set aside.
In same skillet, in remaining 1 tablespoon oil, stir-fry vegetables and garlic until tender-crisp.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place rolls in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan; press into pan for crust.
Fry sausage; pour off grease.
Add onion and fry until tender.
Mix eggs, milk and cheese with seasoning.
Add sausage mixture.
Pour into pan lined with rolls.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: simple salmon pate
directions: In mixing bowl, blend all ingredients until smooth.
Pack into small, oiled bowl.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and garnish with fresh parsley.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine sausage, cheese and croutons.
Layer in bottom of dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over sausage, etc.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
May be frozen before baking.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt in 3-quart bowl; stir in milk.
Microwave on High for 10 to 11 minutes, stirring about every minute and 30 seconds.
Beat egg yolks.
Gradually stir in hot mixture.
Return to microwave; cook on High for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, stirring every 20 seconds.
Remove from microwave and stir in vanilla flavoring.
Let custard cool partly before lining bottom of casserole dish with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour a portion of custard over the bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, bananas and custard, ending with custard on top.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Mix together ingredients until well blended.
Split 1 package hot dogs lengthwise, making sure not to cut completely through the hot dogs.
Spoon some of the barbecue mixture into each hot dog and place in a flat pan, slightly touching each other.
Pour any remaining sauce over the hot dogs.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: steamed crabs "maryland style"
directions: Put water and vinegar in 10-gallon pot.
Place a layer of crabs on an elevated platform in the pot.
Sprinkle each layer generously with seasoning mix.
Put lid on pot and steam about 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned cookies(white)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Then add vinegar
and dry ingredients.
Beat.
Roll into balls size of walnuts.
Press
down
with
bottom of glass.
Dip glass in water or sugar
to prevent sticking.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and margarine in a large bowl using your hands.
After the mixture is smooth, shape into balls and place in a cool area.

title: super fudge
directions: Heat honey and peanut butter.
Quickly add carob and then all the seeds, coconut and fruit.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate until it hardens.
Cut into squares and keep refrigerated.
Yields 25 squares.

title: holiday beef dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except
the walnuts and turn into a shallow greased casserole
dish.
Top
with
the walnuts and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with a selection of crackers.

title: southern fried chicken with gravy
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add milk, salad oil and lemon juice.
Add this mixture to flour mixture and blend.
Pour 2 inches of oil into a large, heavy skillet and heat.
Dip chicken pieces into batter and drop into hot oil.
Reduce heat to medium and fry about 45 minutes, turning frequently to brown all sides of chicken.
Remove chicken to platter.
Pour most of oil from skillet.
Add amount of milk desired for gravy, heat, stirring brown particles from bottom of skillet.

title: joyce's gingerbread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add molasses and water, blending well after each.
Sift all dry ingredients and add, blending well.
Stir in melted shortening and boiling water.
When all ingredients are mixed well, pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When cake is cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar or eat plain.

title: sour cream pecans
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and vanilla in a large pot.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring often.
Pour in roasted pecans.
Stir until liquid is absorbed.
Pour onto waxed paper; separate so pecans will dry without sticking together.
Allow to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: sherbet
directions: Mix in 1 gallon ice cream freezer and churn freezer until hard.
Let sit 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: short 'n sweet peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place peaches in greased shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg; mix with fork and spread over peaches.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix until well blended, add remaining.
Mix well.
Chill overnight. Shape into ball.
Roll in fine chopped nuts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Slice bananas into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange bananas and wafers in the bottom of a large bowl.
Mix milk, cold water and Jell-O in a separate bowl.
In another bowl, whip the cream with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Fold the cream into the pudding mixture. Slice the 3 bananas into 1/2-inch slices and add to pudding mixture.
Next, add the 36 wafers and mix well.
Pour the mixture over the bananas and wafers that have been arranged in the bowl. Garnish the top of the pudding with additional banana slices and wafers.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: steve's snickerdoodles
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt. Mix well.
Roll mixture into balls.
In sandwich bag shake together the 4 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Place balls into bag and shake.
Put balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown in 5-quart Dutch oven:
ground beef, onion, garlic clove and green pepper.
Drain off excess grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, brown sugar, parsley, oregano leaves, salt, cracked pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Partially cover and cook 30 minutes.
Discard the bay leaf.
Best over thin spaghetti noodles.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in broth.
Heat and stir until thick.
Add all other ingredients. Serve over pastry shells.

title: spicy shrimp dip
directions: Cook, peel and chop shrimp into small bite size pieces, enough to make 2 cups; set aside.
Mix chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish (found in the dairy products at most grocers) and lemon juice.
Place cream cheese on platter.
Mix shrimp into sauce and pour over cream cheese.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine flour, sugar and dry yeast in large bowl.
Gradually add warm water and beat until smooth.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Let stand in warm place for 2 days.
To use in bread recipe as directed to replenish starter, add to the remaining starter 1 1/2 cups flour and 1 cup warm water.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and keep in a warm place.
Stir before using.
If not used in 1 week, remove 1 1/2 cups starter and follow directions for replenishing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt
margarine
in casserole dish and add to remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and cheese in casserole dish. Place chicken on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Remove and add grated cheese over top of casserole. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries, orange and orange peel.
Add the sugar and mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Mix the Jell-O and water. When half set, add to cranberry mixture.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and set in refrigerator until completely set.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Cream sugar, oil and eggs until well blended.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes in a cold 350° oven.
Top with glaze.

title: baked salmon in sour cream
directions: Season salmon.
Cover with capers, lemon juice and vinegar. Spread with sour cream.
Arrange slices of lemon on top, sprinkle with seasoned salt and paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: garden vegetable pasta
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook mushrooms and green onions with garlic until tender and liquid is evaporated, stirring often.
Stir in mixed vegetables, tomatoes, half and half, cheese and basil.
Add spaghetti.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: lucky to have any left
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 375° until light brown. Cool completely.

title: confetti pie
directions: In a 9-inch pie pan, mix sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix in butter.
Press mixture firmly and evenly against sides and bottom of pie pan.
Set aside in refrigerator.

title: pa's favorite sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pie shell.
Blend well with electric mixer.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 30 minutes or until golden and puffy.
Top with whipped cream.

title: scampi primavera
directions: Cut carrots into 2-inch thin strips.
Cut zucchini and red pepper into thin strips.
Cook pasta as directed.
Heat oil in large skillet; cook and stir garlic and lemon peel about 30 seconds.
Add vegetables and shrimp.
Stir over medium heat until shrimp turn pink, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Stir in basil and parsley.
Spoon over pasta; toss well.
Serves 8.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and hot water over medium heat until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts are brown and syrup starts to turn.
Add butter and soda.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet (the thinner on sheet the better).

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (save eggs for last and mix one at a time).
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot over medium heat just until starts to boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix rice, ground beef and onion.
Steam cabbage in pot of hot water.
Drain and gently remove leaves.
Put tablespoon of mixture on leaf and roll.
Place in casserole dish.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
(Use water that cabbage was steamed in.)
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a dish.

title: pear butter
directions: Cook 4 hours in crock pot. Put in pint jars and seal.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Break up pretzels.
Mix all other ingredients.
Place pretzels in large baking dish.
Pour mixture evenly over pretzels.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Stir and bake for 10 more minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, eggs, stuffing mix and sage.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into balls.
In dry skillet, brown all sides and drain on paper towels.
Drain fat from skillet.
Add catsup, chili sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and water; stir well.
Return meatballs to skillet; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Refrigerate or may be frozen.
When ready to serve, reheat.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix beef, salt, pepper and A. 1. sauce together.
Form a loaf. Place on a rack over a pan with a small amount of water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until done.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Prepare gravy lite, using double the amount of water called for.
Add vinegar, bay leaf, garlic powder and mushrooms.
Simmer until mushrooms are tender.
Remove from heat.
Crumble meat into the gravy mix.
Stir in the milk and continue to stir until milk is dissolved.
Place 1/2 cup cooked noodles on plate.
Pour meat mixture over all.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Stir
all ingredients together.
Place in casserole and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: amaretto cream
directions: In a 1 to 2-quart pan, sprinkle gelatin over water; let stand for 5 minutes to soften.
Heat over medium heat for 30 seconds or until mixture begins to simmer.
Remove from heat.
In a small mixer bowl, beat eggs on high speed for 2 minutes or until slightly thick.
Slowly beat in sugar, liqueur and gelatin.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream until it mounds softly.
Add egg mixture and fold in to blend.
Pour into a 1-quart mold or into individual serving dishes.
Refrigerate for 3 hours or until mold is set. Unmold onto serving plate or serve from individual dishes.
Garnish with fresh sliced strawberries and mint, if available.
Sprinkle servings with toasted almonds.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped walnuts and place cherry on top.
Garnish with parsley and serve with assorted crackers.
The cheese ball freezes well.

title: easy creamy pasta
directions: Cook the pasta according to the package directions.
Drain well.
Pour the pasta into a large bowl and quickly add the margarine, heavy cream and about half of the Parmesan cheese.
Toss until well mixed.
Serve immediately topped with pepper and the remaining cheese.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Stir together soup, cheese, milk, mayonnaise and eggs.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: In kettle, combine cranberry juice and pectin.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Stir in sugar.
Bring again to boil.
Boil hard, uncovered, 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Skim off foam.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars. Cover with hot wax or water seal.

title: cracker candy
directions: Cover a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet with foil and line with saltine crackers. Boil the butter with the sugar for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour over saltine crackers and bake for 10 minutes at 350° (until bubbly and brown).
Spread the chocolate chips on top and spread until completely covering butter mixture.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Break into small pieces.
Enjoy!
Keep in airtight container.

title: shrimp pasta salad
