directions: Combine bouillon granules, water, white wine, lemon, onion, garlic, bay leaves and red pepper flakes.
Bring to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove shrimp from broth, reserving broth.
Rinse shrimp under cold water.
Chill.
Peel and devein.
Set aside.
Strain broth mixture, reserving 1/2 cup liquid and garlic.
Discard lemon, onion and bay leaves.
Add reserved liquid and cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Rinse under cold water and drain again.

title: jello dessert
directions: Beat the Jell-O; blend in cream and pineapple and set.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Wash and grate zucchini into a bowl.
Mince garlic and shallot and saute in oil until soft.
Wash spinach and shake dry.
Drain off excess moisture from zucchini.
Add with spinach and seasonings to pan and cook until softened and liquid is absorbed.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat butter and cocoa in top of a double boiler until melted. Stir in salt and sugar in small amounts.
Blend well after each portion; then stir in milk and vanilla very slowly.
Cook until it gets thick.

title: pan-fried cabbage
directions: Pan-fried cabbage is simple and delicious.
It can also be incorporated into a vegetarian appetizer or main dish strudel.

title: peppery cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with a hand mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Pack into covered crock and refrigerate.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to other mixture alternating with milk.
Do not overmix.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Fill tins 1/2 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Batter can be made ahead and refrigerated for 3 or 4 days.

title: golden potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, eggs, pimiento and seasonings.
Add combined salad dressing and mustard; mix lightly.
Chill.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread 1/2 can enchilada sauce in 3-quart oblong baking dish. Set aside. Combine chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies and onion. Spread about 1/3 cup mixture along one side of tortilla. Roll jelly roll fashion and place seam side down in dish. Pour remaining 1/2 can of enchilada sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of cheese on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 1 hour.
Add hot dogs.

title: potato ragout
directions: Put bacon in saucepan, cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Drain bacon; dry on paper towels.
Saute bacon in heavy skillet for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are transparent.
Add potatoes, stock, tarragon and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, but not mushy, and liquid is absorbed.
Add vinegar and oil and toss lightly. Sprinkle with parsley; serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: swiss pork chops
directions: Pour over pork chops in baking pan. Bake 1 hour at 375° or until chops are done.
May be used over other meats such as steak, beef or pork roast.

title: birthday party punch
directions: Mix all juices at least 3 hours before.
Pour ginger ale just before serving.
Pour over ice or sherbet.

title: cream taco
directions: Mix all ingredients together in crock-pot except whipping cream.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add whipping cream to mixture 1/2 hour before serving.
Stir.
Serve over Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: parisian sweets
directions: Put fruit and nuts through food chopped, then mix with orange juice and honey.
Press well together and let stand in cool place for 24 hours.
Shape into balls and roll in grated sweet chocolate, coconut or chopped nuts.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour into casserole and top with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter party mix
directions: Melt
margarine,
then	add
sugar.
When
syrupy,
add peanut butter.
Peanut
butter burns easily, so keep stirring over
low heat.
Place cereals, pretzels and nuts in roasting and
baking pans.
(I
use top and bottom of roasting pan and two
x 13-inch pans.) Pour melted mixture over cereals; mix well.	Bake in	a
oven
for
a
couple of hours, until cereals
are dry and crispy.
While baking, mix every 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs and beat well.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture alternately with bananas.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: best meat loaf ever
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape firmly into an 8 x 4-inch loaf; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Blend remaining soup, water and drippings.
Heat; stir occasionally. Serve with meat loaf.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix the dry ingredients; add milk.
Stir and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and creamy (gravy consistency).
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: spinach with crab meat
directions: In a small saucepan, cook spinach over low heat without adding water.
In a skillet heat oil.
Add onion and chilies.
Fry for 3 or 4 minutes until lightly browned.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute. Stir in crab meat and turmeric.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in spinach and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Add salt.
Sprinkle with lime juice and serve immediately with rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Put in saucepan and boil 2 minutes the margarine, butter, sugar and nuts.
Line crackers on cookie sheet. Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake only 7 minutes at 350°, being careful not to burn them.

title: candied carrots with apples
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Place in a greased, 1-quart casserole.
Put apples on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown and white sugar together.
Add egg, water, vanilla, flour, salt and soda.
Beat well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit pizza(great item for a brunch)
directions: Spread cookie dough in a 9-inch pizza pan or cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix sugar with eggs, then add milk.
Stir in flour with the salt and baking powder.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube six cups potatoes. Top off each cup with water, and pour one by one into soup kettle. Slice 1 carrot, 1 stalk celery, and diced 1 onion. Put in cup and top off with water and put in soup kettle. Cook until tender. Add 2 chicken bouillon cubes and simmer until dissolved. Add 1 cup condensed, 1/2 stick butter, and salt and pepper to taste, bring to simmer, serve.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute garlic, onion and bell pepper in oil until tender-crisp. Add rice and brown slightly.
Add tomatoes, then liquid.
Add 1 teaspoon chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until done.

title: beef stew
directions: Dump all the ingredients into crock-pot.
Cover and set on high.
Cook for 6 to 8 hours.
Test for doneness and stir a couple of times.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients. Blend and roll into 1-inch balls. Press into 1/2-inch muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from the oven and press 1
candy into each hot cookie. Allow to cool. Makes 4 dozen.

title: delicious lo-fat quiche
directions: Prepare pastry.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry lined pie plate.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour egg mixture into pie plate.
Cook uncovered in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Cook uncovered until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: love bars
directions: Mix
the
sugar, raisins, water, oleo and cinnamon in a pan and
bring to a boil.
Add the soda dissolved in 1 tablespoon
hot water.
Slowly
boil
5 minutes (watch closely; it will
boil over).
Remove from heat.
Add the chopped nuts and cool.
Sift the
flour	and
baking
powder into mixture; mix well.
Spread into
greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables into pieces.
Put in chopped onions.
Break bacon into small pieces.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Then add all ingredients together; mix well.

title: chocolate chip zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugars, butter and oil in a large bowl. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well. Sift the flour and cocoa into a bowl, then add to sugar mixture. Add grated zucchini and mix well. Mix in chocolate chips, saving some to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 13-inch pan for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Mix the sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt; add to beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in rhubarb; dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until pie is "set" and lightly browned.

title: new year's black-eyed peas and sausage
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain grease, leaving 2 tablespoons in pan.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and garlic to the bacon drippings and saute until onion is clear.
Transfer to Dutch oven and add peas, water, salt, pepper and tomato.
While bringing peas to a boil, fry sausage and drain well.
Add sausage to peas and simmer for 40 minutes or until desired thickness of broth.

title: herbed cheese puffs
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 cup water, butter and salt. Bring to boil, then remove from heat.
Add flour and cayenne pepper all at once and beat vigorously with a wooden spoon until dough is smooth.
Return to low heat and stir continuously for 5 minutes or until the mixture pulls away from the sides and forms a ball.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon, discarding bones.
Combine salmon, bread crumbs, chopped onion, oleo, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Combine milk and egg.
Shape into a loaf and bake at 350° in a greased loaf pan for 35 to 45 minutes.
If desired, serve with cheese sauce.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and fluffy.
Mix sugar and oil; beat into eggs.
Mix together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add to the egg mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Peel and core apples; slice into greased pan 9 x 12-inch.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup of water. Add 1 cup of sugar. Cook 5 minutes or until cranberries split.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, baking soda and cinnamon. Cream butter. Add sugars.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla. Alternate dry ingredients with pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips and raisins. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until firm and lightly browned.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, if skins are tough, otherwise just scrub, rinse and dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a wooden spoon to prevent knife from cutting all the way.
Put in baking dish; fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: liver and onions
directions: Place liver in a strainer. Let cold water run over liver to wash it until it's clear. Place oil in skillet. Heat it slowly. Mix milk and egg; beat well. In another bowl, mix flour, salt and pepper. Place liver in milk mixture, then dip well in flour mixture. Place in hot oil. Turn stove to medium or lower. Cook until liver is brown on both sides, then place your sliced onions on top. Add 1/2 cup water. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour. Turn over once while it steams.

title: jello punch
directions: Heat water, sugar and jello.
Add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Mix well and freeze.
Take from freezer 3 hours before serving and add ginger ale or Sprite just before serving.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let stand while making the crust. Pour mixture into pie crust. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake until a knife comes out clean. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Then at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bacon, egg and cheese casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Arrange buttered bread crumbs on the bottom.
Top with grated cheese, then the meat.
Blend milk and seasonings; pour evenly over bread, cheese and meat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until golden brown on top.
Sausage or ham may be substituted for bacon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook butter in skillet until melted.
Sprinkle in flour.
This makes a paste.
Add broth; stir all together.
Add sour cream. This will be thick and creamy.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Cut
each
wing
at
joint to make 3 pieces, discard the wing tips.
Place
wings
in shallow container.	Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour	over
wings,
reserving 1/4 cup.
Cover and refrigerate
8 to 10 hours, turning occasionally.
Put wings in shallow baking dish and drizzle the reserved 1/4 cup over them. Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add oil, egg yolks, cold water and vanilla or lemon.
Beat well.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix, half of melted butter, milk, cheese and half of garlic powder.
Mix until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Mix remainder of butter and garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: stuffed potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Brush the potatoes all over with oil. Prick them in several place on all sides with a fork. Place in a baking dish. Bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad(low-fat)
directions: Cut vegetables up in large bowl.
Marinate in Kraft free Italian dressing (small bottle).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: In a small saucepan, melt oleo.
Pour into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; spread evenly by tilting.
Sprinkle crushed vanilla wafers evenly over oleo.
Arrange nuts and fruits over crumb mix and press down gently.
Mix sweetened condensed milk and other milk and pour evenly over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 60 squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat (375°) and fry until golden brown.
This makes about 2 dozen.

title: moist n' chewy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large saucepan sprayed with Pam or other pure vegetable cooking spray, over low heat, melt chocolate chips and butter. Stir occasionally until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add baking mix, sweetened condensed milk and egg. Stir well. Stir in walnuts. Spray Pam on bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or dish.
Pour brownie mixture into dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Sprinkle remaining onions over bean mixture. Bake 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Serves 6.

title: sweet cherry relish
directions: Combine all fruits and put through food chopper.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover and let stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Serve as relish for cold meats or as a dessert topping.
Makes 1 pint.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Mix broccoli, onion, soup, mayonnaise, eggs and cheese.
Put into casserole dish.
Cut butter into pieces and arrange over mixture. Crush crackers and cover top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand about 20 minutes before serving.

title: potato crust quiche
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in boiling salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Stir in butter and spoon into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Spread over bottom and up sides, building up sides with a spoon to form a crust.
Arrange vegetables in bottom of potato crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese and sprinkle with bread crumbs or wheat germ.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: arrie's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo over low heat; set aside to cool.
Mix sugar and eggs until slightly fluffy.
Add chocolate, oleo, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Last, add walnuts. Bake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan in a preheated 300° oven.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut into squares.
This recipe may be doubled, if so desired.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt with pastry blender or fork until mixture is consistency of cornmeal.
Sprinkle water over mixture; blend lightly with fork.
Use as little water as possible.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll out between 2 layers of waxed paper, that have been sprinkled with flour.
Makes 2 (8-inch) shells or one double pie crust.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar and milk until fluffy; spread on bottom of pie shell and set aside.

title: chow mein paulene
directions: Brown meat; add soy sauce and 1 cup water.
Simmer, then add onion and celery.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Blend cornstarch and water and add to mixture.
Add chestnuts, mushrooms and bean sprouts. Heat through.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into well-oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: corn-stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut a pocket in each chop.
Or use butterfly chops.
Season cavity with salt and pepper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Shake biscuits in this mixture (cut biscuits in quarters before shaking in the mixture).
Arrange in angel cake pan.
Boil brown sugar, oleo and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Put
all
dry
ingredients
in bowl and add oil, water, pumpkin and eggs.
Add nuts last.
Grease and flour 5 small or 2 large
baking pans.
Divide batter into pans and bake 1 hour at 350° or until top is no longer moist.

title: sour cream cheese enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in oil until soft.
Place some cheese and onion in each shell and roll.
Place, seam side down, in lightly greased cake size pan.

title: sweet and sour chicken and rice
directions: Cut up chicken into cubes.
Put in skillet and cook until chicken is no longer pink.
Add all ingredients and cook on low heat. Boil rice and mix rice with chicken mixture.

title: roll-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add the egg, salt and vanilla. Blend in the flour.
Refrigerate dough at least 1 hour before using (can be overnight).
Roll thin on floured surface.
Cut out cookies.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Decorate or frost.

title: seasoned seeds
directions: Remove membrane from seeds.
Wash and pat dry.
Place in a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Add remaining ingredients.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes until slightly toasted, stirring 4 to 5 times.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Beginning with lettuce, layer each ingredient on top of the other in oblong dish.
Spread the mayonnaise over the layer of hard-boiled eggs.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top of mayonnaise.
Add bacon bits if desired.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Break the cauliflower and broccoli into small flowerets into a bowl.
Cut up onion
real
fine
and
then
add chopped tomatoes. Mix together the
mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix well and chill.

title: pillsbury oreo cake and icing
directions: Mix cake and add cookie crumbs.
Bake in layers or 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing or frost in the pan.

title: pennies from heaven
directions: Mix tomato soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over cooked carrots, bell pepper and onions.
Toss slightly and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Dissolve coffee and cinnamon in hot water.
Mix all ingredients together with a hand-held mixer until desired spreading consistency.

title: sweet broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into florets and chop some of the stems into small pieces. Mix broccoli, raisins, pecans and onion in a salad bowl. Refrigerate. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in a bowl. Let stand, covered, in the refrigerator overnight. Pour dressing over the salad just before serving.

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Stir by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven until glossy and set, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: crabbies
directions: Split muffins.
Mix all ingredients and spread on 12 muffin halves, then cut each muffin half into eight.
Broil or freeze (then heat).

title: cranberry pork chops(serves 4)
directions: Flour chops and brown in a small amount of hot oil in skillet. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until fork tender.

title: smoke sausage and cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in quarters; cut sausage in 2-inch lengths.
In
a large pot, pour in 3 cups water, 1 tablespoon salt and sausage pieces.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Reduce heat; put cabbage in water and cover.
Cabbage should be done in about 25 minutes.

title: crunchy potato balls
directions: In a bowl, combine the potatoes, ham, cheese, mayonnaise, egg, mustard and pepper; mix well.
Add enough of the flour to make a stiff mixture.
Chill.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in cornflakes.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until heated through. Serve hot.

title: maple pecan-glazed sweet potatoes(low-fat)
directions: In small bowl, combine 2 tablespoons of the apple juice and the cornstarch; mix well.
Set aside.
In large skillet or Dutch oven, combine remaining apple juice, syrup, cinnamon, margarine and salt; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; stir to coat well. Return to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or just until potatoes are tender.
Stir cornstarch mixture into potato mixture; cook and stir over medium-high heat until bubbly and thickened.* Pour into ungreased 8-inch square (1 1/2-quart) baking dish; cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Pour all ingredients into a pint jar with a tight lid.
Shake well, until mixed.
Set in refrigerator for a few days (the longer, the better).
This thickens with age.
Use on fruit, cole slaw or just over lettuce.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 8 servings. prep time: 15 minutes.)
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave, allowing about 5 minutes per potato to cook.
When soft, let cool and peel into measuring cup.
Use about 3 cups of potatoes.
Put stick of butter on top and put back into microwave and melt butter into potatoes.
Add dash of salt, cinnamon and sugar and blend with mixer.
Add eggs and mix well. Mix in vanilla.
Add condensed milk and blend well.
Stir in coconut (optional) and blend.
Pour into 3 frozen pie shells and bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes or until center is set.

title: amaretto pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add sugar and flavorings.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Stir in flour.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: german potato salad
directions: Place potatoes, onions, eggs and parsley in a greased casserole or baking pan.
Pour dressing over potato mixture and mix to coat all.
Heat oven to 350° and cook for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: turkey slow grilled
directions: Preheat covered barbecue grill to 300°.
Move coals to side and place pan large enough to catch all drippings under the grate. Wash and pat dry bird.
Blend herbs and butter to a paste. (Experiment with whatever herbs you like or, better yet, fresh herbs!)
Separate the skin from the breast from the back.
Insert paste and rub between the skin and meat.
Grill for 10 minutes per pound.
Fresh cooks faster!
Turkey is so moist and tender!

title: nevada beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion about 10 minutes.
Combine with rest of ingredients and pour into greased 2 quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pineapple or any other fruit pie
directions: Stir all above ingredients together.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add milk and bring to boil.
Pour beaten egg yolks in and cook until it thickens.
Add extract, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Brown in oven.

title: taco seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients in small bowl.
Add to 1 1/2 cups of water and 1 pound cooked hamburger.
Simmer for 10 minutes just as you would packaged seasoning.

title: cheese cake
directions: CRUST:
Mix first three ingredients and place in spring form pan.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix together cheese and sugar.
Fold in berries, bananas, pineapple and walnuts.
Blend in 12 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before you serve.

title: party punch
directions: Combine juices and water.
Stir until thawed, add 2 trays ice cubes.
Just before serving, carefully pour the ginger ale and club soda into bowl.
Makes 25 servings.

title: kentucky chocolate pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: little pizzas
directions: Mix together tomato paste, sugar, salt, garlic and Worcestershire sauce and spread thinly on muffins. Sprinkle cheese over tomato mixture. Top with pepperoni.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Crush Ritz and line bottom of casserole.
Drain peas and layer half over crackers.
Drain asparagus; layer half over peas. Sprinkle half of cheese over all.
Add half cream of mushroom soup.
Repeat layer, peas, asparagus, mushroom soup.
Bake at 375° to 400° until bubbly.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top and bake 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Baking time:
45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in cream
directions: Rub chicken breasts with poultry seasoning.
Saute in butter and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove to a buttered casserole dish.
Cover with the ham and a slice of cheese on each piece of chicken, parsley and thyme to taste.
Pour heavy cream over all and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Then broil for 5 minutes until light brown.
Serve with Wild Rice Sausage Bake.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees (if using Tube or Bundt Pan 325 degrees).
Cream Butter and Sugar.
Add Eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with Milk, then beat well.
Add Vanilla.
Turn into greased pan for 25 minutes or in Tube pan for 1 hour.
Ice with your favorite icing and give thanks for God's Blessings.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Place batter in pan; then add nuts.
Then add syrup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill well (may be chilled overnight).
Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.
Can be frozen.

title: devilishly decadent pudding cake(low fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat 8 inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray, set aside.
In mixer bowl beat milk and prune puree to blend thoroughly; add flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat just to blend thoroughly. Spread evenly in pan.
In small bowl,
mix brown sugar and the remaining 1/4 c. cocoa powder.
Sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake in center of oven about 45 minutes until cake is springy to the touch.
Cool 15 minutes on rack.

title: easy butterscotch pecans rolls
directions: Melt margarine in small pan and set aside.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle pecans over the bottom.
Arrange frozen rolls in pan over nuts, 4 across and 6 down.
Sprinkle pudding (dry) over rolls.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar mix over top.
Pour melted margarine over the rolls.
Let stand overnight covered with wax paper.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Turn upside down on cookie sheet.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown, drain and crumble hamburger with onion and garlic added.
Cook noodles.
In skillet, mix meat, corn, soup, tomato sauce and chili powder and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Layer the noodles, cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese twice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: May add chocolate chips, butterscotch chips or anything else.

title: cheesy broiled appetizers
directions: Mix cheese, bacon bits, mayonnaise, olives and onions.
Spread 1 tablespoon over each bread slice.
Broil until cheese melts, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle bottom with coconut, then pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over coconut and pecans. Beat until creamy, remaining ingredients and spoon over other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork & sauerkraut supper
directions: Layer in casserole.
Pour beer on top.
Bake at 325 degrees for 2 hours.

title: white chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until ready to serve.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well.
Stir in jam, add flour which has been sifted with spices, alternately with sour cream and ending with flour.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in four 9-inch layers in 350° oven until center springs back when pressed with finger.
(May also be baked in a tube pan.)
Frost with Never Fail Frosting.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Put chicken in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top.
Inset lemon in cavity.
Bake, breast up, at 350° for 1 hour, breast down at 350° for 1/2 hour and breast up at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Boil 4 to 6 large chicken pieces until chicken falls off bones. Use the 2 quarts water to boil chicken in.
Cut up onion and place in with chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and 1 sprig of thyme. Add okra, cut in cubes.
Add tomatoes.
At this point you can add shrimp, crab or sausage or leave it with just the chicken.
Boil slowly for 3 hours.
To be eaten with rice.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Mix together sugars, ketchup, barbecue sauce, pepper, mustard, chili powder and salt.
Stir into kidney beans, lima beans, pork and beans and ground beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey lemon barbecued chicken
directions: Mix well honey, lemon juice mustard and salt.
Barbecue chicken over medium hot coals and brush generously with glaze mixture.
(Sometimes I marinate in a Ziploc bag in mixture for an hour before barbecue.)
Cook chicken until fork tender.
Brush often with honey glaze.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat milk and butter; add cracker crumbs.
Add other ingredients, except butter.
Take out stem of mushrooms; fill with stuffing.
Dip mushrooms in butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pat's appetizers
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnut; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until bacon is done.

title: coach's delight
directions: Nabisco Snack Wells (optional) may be substituted for the fat gram counters.

title: easy white sauce
directions: Forget all that butter and flour and beating to get rid of lumps!
This is the easy low-fat way.
Mix dry ingredients together thoroughly.
Add water slowly.
Heat over slow heat (or higher heat for the brave, but stir constantly).
Cook until it bubbles.
Add salt, pepper or other spices of your choice.
Add cubes of yellow cheese to make a cheese sauce.
I sometimes add the cheese, a dab of mustard and serve over macaroni.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead and make into small balls. Place pecan on each ball to flatten.
Bake at 350° for about 14 to 16 minutes.

title: italian sausages and peppers
directions: Fry sausages in 1/2 cup oil for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and slice when cool.
In same oil that sausages were cooked in, add sliced onions and peppers.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and sausages and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste (garlic salt and parsley may also be added to taste).

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together, knead lightly. Ready to use or eat!

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Quarter each biscuit and place in a bowl (large).
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Place lid on bowl and shake well.
Melt butter; pour over mixture in bowl.
Add 1 more cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Shake well.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: judy's pancakes
directions: In large bowl, combine yeast, water and teaspoon of sugar. Add mixture of eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Combine all dry ingredients in a second bowl and add them to the liquid.
Fry pancake batter as desired.

title: chess pie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter together.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream sugar, cheese and 3 eggs together.
Pour on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar.
Pat into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: karen's banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla. Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture alternately with bananas, rum and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes two 8-inch layers or 1 loaf.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: strawberry-nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat until smooth and creamy. Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli ham quiche
directions: Place hash browns in a greased 9-inch microwave-safe dish. Microwave, uncovered, on high for 4 minutes or until thawed.
Press onto botom and halfway up the sides of rhe dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on high 3 minutes, sprinkle with cheese, ham and broccoli.
In a bowl, beat the eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over the ham mixture.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at 70% power for 10-12 minutes or until set.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.
Yield:
4-6 servings.

title: olive burger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet; drain well. Add onions, garlic salt, pepper and water. Cook until dry. Layer meat, olives, cheese and sliced tomatoes in bottom crust. Repeat, then cover with top crust. Make 3 or 4 holes near center of top crust with a fork to help vent the pie. Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vanilla and egg together.
Put fruit in bottom of pan.
Pour egg mixture over it.
Add butter and cut in pieces.
Cover with dough.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Brown chicken in a little oil in a large Dutch oven.
Drain oil and add all other ingredients and stir well.
Cover and cook slowly until chicken is done.
Serve with unsalted rice.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Combine oleo and brown sugar in saucepan, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until brought to boil.
Boil for one minute. Add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to second boil and remove from heat; cool.
Mix in powdered sugar.
If too thick, add small amounts of evaporated milk.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add brown sugar and white sugar. Add one egg at a time.
Beat until well creamed.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and vanilla, then add nuts.
Blend well. Place mixture in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour.
Test for doneness.

title: caramel krispie treats
directions: Unwrap approximately 60 caramels.
Microwave with 3 tablespoons of water in a glass mixing bowl, stirring constantly, so caramels don't stick or burn.
Add Rice Krispies, 1 cup at a time, while stirring.
Pat mixture into a glass casserole, after spraying with Pam.

title: berry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients
into small mixing bowl.
Add egg, milk and melted butter.
Stir
just until blended.
Fold in berries. Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake
20 to 25 minutes at 400°. Makes 1 dozen.
I have found that when
I
use frozen berries, they get nicer if I reduce the milk to 1/3 cup.

title: mrs. dobias' kit kat bar
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Club crackers, and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Club crackers; pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Add layer of Club crackers; pour mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of Club crackers.
Then top with Topping.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Pour hot water over 1/2 cup sugar; stir.
Add yeast and let dissolve.
Scald milk with shortening.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add salt.
Beat eggs until light.
Add to milk and yeast.
Mix well.

title: chicken salad oriental
directions: Remove strings from pea pods and cut diagonally in half.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar and soy sauce in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: poor man's cookie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and raisin mixture.
Sift flour and other ingredients.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour strawberry soda into ice cube trays; freeze.
Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes; add fruit juices and chill.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Dice tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Tear lettuce into small bits.
Mix with salad dressing and serve.

title: candy apple walnut pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts & candies, 2/3 c. sugar & 1/3 c. flour.
Pour into 1 frozen pie crust.
Break or crumble second pie crust and toss with remaining 2 Tbsp. of sugar and 1 Tsp. cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in preheated 375° oven on a preheated baking sheet for 55-60 mins. or until candies melt and bubble up.
Cool completely before serving.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and add apricots, marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Let set.
Cook together last 6 ingredients; let sauce cool and then fold in 1 cup whipped cream. Spread over Jell-O.
You can put grated cheese or coconut on top.

title: lebanese potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Do not overcook.
Cool until you can handle them.
Peel and salt while still warm.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly.
Add to diced potatoes.
Mix and chill until served.

title: pineapple angel food trifle
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice; set aside.
Combine pudding mix, 1/2 cup reserved juice and milk in a large bowl; beat at low speed 2 minutes or until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple tidbits.
Place 1/3 of cake cubes in the bottom of 16 ounce glass bowl, drizzle with 2 to 3 tablespoons remaining pineapple juice.
Spoon 1/3 of pudding mixture over cake.
Repeat process twice, ending with pudding mixture.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix well.
Divide between 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat;
add sugar and beat well. Add eggs
one at a time;
beat well after each one.
Add flour and beat
well;
add
vanilla and nuts.
Pour into Pam sprayed pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Good stuff.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add water, eggs, and pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.
When cool, serve with whipped cream.
This bread freezes well.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake, stirring once, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna mac and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Mix in remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart microwavable serving dish. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir casserole and continue heating on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Preparation time: 20 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Cube potatoes.
Toss in a large mixing bowl with other ingredients until well coated.
Bake at 300° to 325°, uncovered, in a large casserole dish for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir once halfway through.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts in boiling salted water until tender. Drain, reserving 2 cups broth.
Let chicken cool and set aside. Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling salted water; drain and set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly; gradually stir in broth, whipping cream and sherry.
Continue to cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Arrange broccoli in 13 x 9 inch baking dish; top with 1/2 sauce.
Arrange chicken pieces over broccoli.
Stir 1/4 cup parmesan cheese into remaining sauce and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle on the 2 Tbsp. parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes; then broil for 2 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists rolls
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon. Roll biscuits, each to a 9-inch rope.
Bring ends together and seal. Dip in melted butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Twist.
Place on greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake in a 450° oven for about 10 minutes. Makes 10 rolls.

title: cream cheese cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cake mix, butter, 1 egg and nuts. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over pressed mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until barely brown.

title: yakitori(japanese)
directions: Soak chicken in combined sauces for 20 minutes or longer.
Put 4 or 5 pieces of chicken on bamboo stick.
Simmer down remaining sauce until quantity is half.
May need to use a little cornstarch in water to thicken.
Broil on charcoal grill.
Brush several times.
(Buy mirin in Oriental food store; purchase Oriental grater.
Saki is found in wine specialty stores.)

title: sour cream-glazed pecans
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream in a heavy 1 1/2 to 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and cook about 5 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add pecans and stir to coat well.

title: easy chicken dish
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Salt lightly, if desired.
Add onions.
Mix soup and sherry; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler (or on low power in microwave).
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Cool slightly.
Stir in brandy (or Kahlua or any flavored liquer). Beat egg whites into stiff peaks.
Fold whites into the chocolate mixture, gently blending.
Spoon into 8 separate dishes or 1 large dish.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate curls.

title: honey orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken into strips and dip into orange juice.
Roll strips in bread crumbs and bake for 30 minutes.
Use an aluminum foil covered pan.
Boil 1 cup water and stir in bouillon cube, then 1/2 small jar of honey.
Take chicken out of oven; pour chicken broth over the top.
Leave uncovered and bake for another 30 minutes.
Be sure to baste chicken every 5 minutes, until desired thickness is reached.
Serve on a bed of rice and French-cut green beans.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer the coconut and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan (do not stir).
Mix the cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over pecans (do not stir).
Mix the powdered sugar, softened cream cheese and softened margarine.
Drop on top of cake mixture by tablespoon (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crumble 2/3 package of cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
In large bowl, mix together pudding and milk.
Combine cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture; blend well.
Pour over cookies. Crumble remaining cookies and sprinkle on top.
Chill before serving.

title: million dollar salad(frozen salad)
directions: Mix first five items.
Cut cherries in half and mix Cool Whip. Put in refrigerator until it gels.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar mixed with orange juice and a lump of butter.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Stir
milk
into flour and salt.
Beat egg slightly and add to	batter.
Add water.
Beat well to cause bubbles.
Let sit and rebeat at intervals.
Put
a
teaspoon of hot meat fat into round 8 or 9-inch
tin
and
heat
tin
in oven.	Pour in batter and bake at 425° for about 15 minutes, reducing oven to 350° for 15 minutes
longer.
Batter should rise like popovers and be served with roast beef and pan gravy.

title: corn dogs
directions: You will need 8 popsicle or wiener sticks.

title: danish potato salad
directions: Heat butter and cook onion over slow heat.
Add salt, pepper, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil and add cream.
Mix well and slowly add potatoes while blending.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve warm.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter, shortening and sugar until soft and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs and juice from fruit cocktail.
Mix well. Add fruit and stir. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar, nuts and oleo.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes.
Ice with Fruit Cocktail Icing.

title: baked tuna-stuffed potatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste. Dip in flour and fry in hot grease until browned on both sides.
Take up on paper towels to absorb excess grease.
Serve hot.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook salt pork in 3-quart saucepan, stirring occasionally, until crisp.
Stir in onion and bell pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 14 minutes.
Do not lift cover or stir. Remove from heat.
Fluff lightly with fork.
Cover and let steam 5 to 10 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: *If using plain flour, add 2 teaspoons baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil cupcake liners.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed on mixer until well blended; add eggs, mix well.
Pour into muffin cups over wafers, fill 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°. Chill.
Top with fruit, preserves if desired.

title: gazpacho
directions: Peel, seed and chop tomatoes into 1/4-inch pieces.
Peel, seed and dice cucumbers likewise.
(The finer the dice the more elegant the results, the time is worth it.
Don't use a food processor.) Chop pepper and scallions very fine.
Dice garlic very fine.
Mash lightly and add to oil and vinegar.
Pour over the vegetables. Add tomato juice and beef broth.
Season with hot pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Chill overnight to allow flavors to blend. Serve cold.
Boiled, chilled shrimp may be added to serving bowls.

title: polynesian turkey
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Toss lightly. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Before serving, slice banana. Add to turkey mixture with nuts.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish with coconut and oranges.

title: southern yam casserole
directions: Arrange yams, apple and dates in greased, shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, flavoring, nutmeg, walnuts and brown sugar.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake in 350° (moderate) oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bowl. Roll biscuits in mixture.
Place biscuits in a greased tube pan. Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. This is really great for breakfast.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix well together; let stand several hours or overnight.

title: sour cream cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder and add alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring and blend well.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: potato filling
directions: Peel, cook and mash potatoes.
Saute onion, celery, parsley and marjoram flakes until tender.
Beat eggs.
Add to mashed potatoes (no milk).
Then add rest of ingredients and bake if desired.

title: fantastic focaccia bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll crust onto flat baking stone. Spread with garlic. Grate 1/2 of Romano cheese, 1/3 cup over crust with deluxe cheese grater. Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 1 teaspoon oregano.
Top with tomatoes, remaining Mozzarella and oregano.
Grate remaining Romano cheese over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly. Yield: 8 servings.

title: strawberry-rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, heat mixture to a boil and boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pour into small sterilized jars.
Cover and let cool.
When cool, store in freezer.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken
and
debone it.
Mix crackers, poppy seed and melted
margarine
in
large
bowl.
Mix
deboned chicken, cream of	chicken
soup and sour cream in another bowl.
Layer 1/2 of Ritz
mixture
for	crust in bottom of casserole dish. Next, put in	the
chicken, soup and sour cream mixture.
Put remaining cracker
mixture
on
top.	Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Put rice and water in bottom of pan.
Place chicken on rice. Mix soups together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours in covered pan.
Remove cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: "surprise me" fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; sprinkle with fajita seasoning, salt and flour and put into hot oil.

title: big cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients using mixer; add remaining ingredients mixing by hand.
Drop by very large spoonfuls-making six cookies to a cookie sheet.
Bake 12-15 minutes at 350 F.

title: gourmet casserole
directions: Mix together and put in casserole dish.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine.
Crush 1 package Town House crackers and mix with margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta with bay scallops
directions: Cook pasta; drain and toss lightly with olive oil to prevent sticking.
Set aside.
Lightly beat egg yolks; add half and half, salt, pepper and cayenne or Tabasco.
Chop fresh parsley; add and mix all until blended.
Set aside in a large bowl.
In a large frying pan, saute the pasta and scallops.
When the scallops turn opaque, add zucchini, eggplant and peppers.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly.
When the vegetables are hot, add the mixture to the bowl with the eggs and cream.
Stir vigorously.
When it begins to thicken, add cheese.
Mix well.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed with electric mixer until thick and lemon colored.
Add butter and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until filling is set.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: mom's date crumbles
directions: Mix together with fingers the flour, soda, oatmeal and brown sugar.
Add margarine.
Mix well and line a greased 9 x 13-inch pan (cover bottom well).

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, onion, bell pepper; salt and pepper to taste. Place in a 9 x 13 pan. Pour half of margarine over mixture; add bacon crumbles, if desired. Heat and stir sour cream, cream of chicken soup, and Cheez Whiz until mixed good; pour on top of potatoes. Add crushed corn flakes. Add remaining half of margarine on top. Bake at 350° 1 hour or until done.

title: horns
directions: Mix flour and salt in large bowl.
Take yeast and crumble over flour and salt.
Add butter and lard (make substance like pie dough)
Make hole in middle of dough and put egg yolks, eggs and sour cream into it.
Mix with hands.

title: pecan pie
directions: Turn on oven at 375° (high moderate). Beat eggs slightly in 2-quart bowl. Stir in sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir in pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake near center of oven 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is slightly firm. Center of pie may look soft when pie is gently shaken but will become firm when pie cools.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onions.
Add onions to beef broth; cook for 10 minutes.
Pour into ovenproof bowls.
Lay sliced French bread on top of soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and broil until cheese is golden.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour mixed with soda and baking powder.
Add mashed bananas and pecans and mix well.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 3/4 to 1 hour. When persimmons are in season, you may substitute them for the bananas.
One cup of peeled mashed persimmons equals 2 medium ripe bananas.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix broth, soup and vegetables together. Then add chicken.

title: pig cake
directions: This is a large cake.
I use a 12-inch spring-form pan. Single ten-inch is too small.
Great for a special party.
Serves 16.

title: baked bananas from africa
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cut the bananas in half lengthwise.
Put in an ovenproof dish, with the cut sides facing up.
Melt the butter or margarine in a pan over a low heat.
Stir in the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over the bananas.
Cover with dish with aluminum foil and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pittsburg pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook beef until brown; drain grease. Add onion, garlic salt, spaghetti sauce and undrained mushrooms. Mix well. Pour half of the cooked macaroni into deep casserole and cover with half of the tomato sauce. Spread half of the sour cream over the tomato sauce.
Top with all of the Provolone cheese. Repeat the layers. Top with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove cover and bake until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: party surprise
directions: Slice off top of cake (1/2-inch thick). Scoop out a cavity all the way around the cake.
Mix half of the Cool Whip and the package of strawberries together (reserve 2 or 3 strawberries). Empty into the cavity of the cake.
Put top back on. Frost with remaining Cool Whip, then put leftover strawberries on top.

title: raspberry creme
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add berries and ice cream.
Mix until smooth.
Chill.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening. Add eggs.
Add soda to sour cream, then add this to egg mixture. Combine flour, baking powder and salt together and sift.
Add gradually to egg mixture. Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as shown on package.
Drain and put into dish. Stir in soup and cheese.
Mix together the cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of vegetables.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Gradually add the sugar to the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.
After baked, turn oven off and leave it in overnight.

title: applesauce
directions: Core apples and slice into quarters.
Place in a saucepan with water.
Cook slowly until apples are tender, about 20 minutes. Put apples through a food mill and discard skins (if mill is not available, peel apples before cooking and after cooking, mash them).
Add cinnamon and lemon juice.
If desired, add sugar, but it is not necessary.

title: honey spice bars
directions: Add sugar to egg.
Add oil and honey to fill cup.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla.
Combine with honey mixture.
If egg is large and vanilla is generous, the dough may be a little weak.
Add 1/4 cup more flour.
The dough should be stiff.
Press dough into pre-greased large pan, 11 x 16-inch. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
On removing from oven, have already prepared the slightly runny glaze.
Ice when cookies are still very hot.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and flavoring. Be careful not to add too much milk and flavoring or the mixture will be soupy.
Add Cool Whip and blend with mixer until creamy. Divide mixture between the two pie shells.
Gently spoon half of cherry pie filling over top of mixture.
Cover pies with plastic top from pie shells.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pat cary's refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour
boiling
water
over
salt,
sugar and shortening. Stir and
cool.
Add
yeast
to
water;
put
yeast and egg in mixture. Stir in flour to make soft dough.
Rub top with solid shortening. Cover
loosely.
Put in refrigerator (keeps 3 to 4 days).
Put out about 2 hours before use.
Make into rolls, let rise.
Bake at 450° until browned.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in Eagle Brand milk. Mix well and pour into freezer and add enough milk to fill container.
Mix this ahead and sit in the freezer; when ready to make ice cream, you'll be ready.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Skin tomatoes if fresh.
Place in large skillet on top burner at medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar to taste (some days I like less, sometimes more) approximately 1/2 to 3/4 cup.
Cook until it becomes thick and clear; add lump of butter, size of walnut (about 3 tablespoons).
Add dumplings and continue to cook until done.
Add seasonings (salt, pepper and basil).
Remove from fire and stir in a drizzle of evaporated milk (1/4 to 1/2 cup).

title: quick crisp lemon cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream shortening; add sugar and pudding mix.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Add flour mixture; beat thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco dip by suzie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread into dish.
Pour picante sauce on top.
Sprinkle cheese on sauce and put tomatoes on top of the cheese. Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: nutty rice stuffing or casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery, mushrooms, shallots, garlic, scallions and parsley in butter until limp.
Add water chestnuts, walnuts and herbs and cook over low heat for about 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix with cooked rice and cool slightly.
Combine egg and broth and stir into rice mixture along with prunes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Use as stuffing or a side casserole.
Makes 4 cups or stuffs a 4 to 5 pound roasting chicken.
If used as a side casserole, put in 1 1/2-inch high roasting pan; oil the top and bake until golden on top (1/2 hour approximately).

title: angel feathers
directions: Cook until thick, in a double boiler, the white sugar, beaten egg yolks and milk.
When cooled somewhat,
but still medium hot, add unflavored gelatin, cold water and vanilla.
Let cool until solid.
Then fold in packages of Dream Whip and egg whites and beat until stiff with mixer (at low speed).
Set aside.

title: darrell's goulash
directions: Brown meat in oil and season with salt.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add water, soup base, salt and paprika.
Cook until meat is tender (falling apart).
Add tomatoes.
Heat to boiling. Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to broth to thicken.
Serve over noodles.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: Cut chicken and fry with onion and garlic.
When done, add tomatoes and water.
Boil 5 minutes; add bay leaf, salt, rice saffron (seasoning out of yellow rice) and green peppers.
Stir thoroughly and place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Garnish with the pimentos and can peas.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: log cabin dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in a little cold water and mix into hot milk. Let set until cool.
Stir in whipped cream and pecans.
Pour into dish lined with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Top with a few crumbs. Chill thoroughly.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Grind egg, salt, juice and mustard for 70 seconds.
Add oil while motor is running.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: grandma's chicken casserole
directions: Grease 12x9 baking dish.
Pour rice in bottom of dish, put chicken on top of rice.
Pour onion soup mix over chicken and rice.
Heat mushroom soup and water until hot, and pour over top. Add butter, and bake at 375° for 1-1/2 hrs. or until done.

title: grilled honey chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breast halves on a preheated barbecue grill for 20 to 30 minutes or until cooked through.
Meanwhile, in a medium-sized bowl, combine the remaining ingredients, then brush over cooked chicken and grill for 5 minutes more.

title: coconut pie(2 pies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until done.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Mix ingredients together.
Pour half of the
batter into pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Sprinkle
over
batter in pan.
Pour other half of batter in pan.
Bake
to
minutes	or until cake is golden brown or springs back at touch.

title: sausage soup
directions: In skillet, crumble and brown sausage.
Pour off grease. Transfer sausage to very large stock pot.
Add tomato juice, tomatoes, green beans, butter beans, okra and carrots.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes. Cook for 15 minutes.
Add corn and peas.
Cook 15 more minutes. Serve hot with cornbread.
Leftovers freeze well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add cheese last.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: firecracker casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion, cumin and chili powder; drain off fat.
Put meat mixture in pan.
Layer with the beans.
Top with Ro-Tel and soup, then add the tortillas.
Finish with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roach killer
directions: Add water to form small balls.
Place all around.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter with 1 1/2 c. sugar; add dates, lemon juice and milk.
Cook until soft and mushy.
Beat eggs.
Add to fruit mixture with vanilla and salt.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts; cool. Shape into balls and roll into coconut, chopped nuts or powdered sugar.

title: mix-in-the-pan chocolate-date cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare Chocolate Chip Topping (below); reserve.
Pour hot water over dates in small bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain dates, reserving water.
Mix flour, brown sugar, cocoa, baking soda, and salt in ungreased square pan, 8x8x2 inches.
Stir in dates.
Add enough water to date water to measure 1 cup.
Stir water mixture and remaining ingredients into flour mixture.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: coconut dream bars
directions: Mix ingredients well and put into a 9 x 12-inch ungreased pan. Bake 15 minutes, or until slightly browned, in a moderate oven.

title: easy time holiday squares
directions: Add sugar to butter in mixing bowl; cream well until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and lemon extract.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Mark off into 20 squares, making holes with teaspoon carefully.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of pie filling in each center.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift powdered sugar over squares. Cut into 20 squares.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple in a heavy saucepan. Stir well.
Cook over medium heat 15 or 20 minutes or until the cranberry skins begin to pop.
Stir in the pineapple; reduce heat to low and cook an additional 30 minutes, stirring often.
Serve warm or cold.

title: patio blush
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; divide among six 16-ounce glasses.
Fill glasses with ginger ale.
Top each with a scoop of sherbet.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: flowerpot fruitcake
directions: To prepare flower pots:
Use 3 new clay pots that are 4 inches wide at the top (inside rim) and 4 1/2 inches in depth.
Pull off a 12-inch square of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Turn clay pot over and press foil as smoothly as possible over bottom and up sides of outside of pot.
Remove shaped foil, then turn clay pot over and carefully press foil down into pot firmly and smoothly against insides of pot.
Press extra foil over rim of pot for easy lifting later.
Grease bottom and side of foil; dust with flour.

title: wine sauced beans and franks(from 1975 edition)
directions: Place franks in saucepan with wine.
Cover and heat slowly to simmer.
Turn off heat.
Let stand to plump up.
Cut a lengthwise gash in top of each frank.

title: grilled vegetable kabobs with rice
directions: Combine dressing, parsley and basil in a small bowl, cover and chill.
Alternate squash, onions, tomatoes and mushrooms on 8 skewers.

title: ma schell's sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with wet hand.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter french toast
directions: Spread peanut butter evenly over 4 bread slices.
Arrange banana slices evenly over peanut butter.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and milk in shallow dish.
Melt butter in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Dip each sandwich into egg mixture, turning to coat both sides.
Place in hot skillet and cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until brown. Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans; over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together; stand overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown onion and meat together and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except beans.
Add meat mixture and beans with other ingredients. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add beaten eggs, sour cream and soda.
Beat well; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together except sour cream.
Fold sour cream in last. Grease ovenproof dish lightly (deep pie plate).
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut bananas
directions: Cut bananas into 1-inch pieces.
Place the lemon juice, sour cream and coconut into separate bowls. Dip banana pieces into the lemon juice.
Roll in sour cream and then in coconut.
Make sure all sides are covered.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate several hours. Makes 24 pieces.

title: broccoli ring
directions: Cook and drain the chopped broccoli.
Soften gelatin in water. Add condensed chicken broth to gelatin; heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Beat mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and minced onion with rotary beater until smooth.
Add gelatin and beat again.
Fold eggs and broccoli into partially set gelatin mixture.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill.
For small crowd, halve ingredients.

title: frozen buttermilk salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown, drain and rinse hamburg.
Fry onions.
Can also add 2 large green peppers, diced.
Mix catsup, sugar, chili powder, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Mix and place in electric roaster. Simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring often.
Serves 80 to 85.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in tube pan at 325° until done.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Coat beef in first 4 ingredients, brown.
Add onion and garlic, cook until soft.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add potatoes and carrots, cook another 45 minutes.

title: elom teriyaki chicken wings and fried rice
directions: Cut chicken wings into drumettes.
Discard tips or freeze for chicken stock.
Wash chicken.
Combine the light soy sauce, teriyaki sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Heat oil in deep fryer or skillet.
Drain chicken and fry.

title: chinese fried walnuts
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving or up to 2 weeks ahead: In a 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling.
Add walnuts and heat to boiling; cook 1 minute.
Rinse walnuts under running hot water.
Drain.
Wash saucepan and dry well.
In a large bowl with a rubber spatula, gently stir warm walnuts with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
(If necessary, let mixture stand 5 minutes to dissolve sugar.)
Meanwhile, in same saucepan over medium heat, heat about 1 inch salad oil to 350°.
With a slotted spoon, add about half of walnuts to oil; fry 5 minutes or until golden, stirring often.

title: oven-fried parmesan chicken
directions: Melt margarine and set aside.
Combine stuffing, Parmesan cheese, parsley and garlic.
Dip chicken into margarine.
Roll in stuffing mixture.
Arrange, skin side up, in shallow baking pan. Do not crowd.
Sprinkle with margarine and stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: marie hardegree's vanilla wafers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to butter mixture and blend well.
Stir in raisins or pecans, if desired.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Allow room to spread.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: super nachos
directions: Arrange chips in single layer on large microwave plate. Sprinkle cheese evenly over chips.
Spoon teaspoonfuls of beans over chips; top with 1/2 teaspoonful of salsa.
Microwave at medium (50%) 1 1/2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; cut in eighths and arrange in 9-inch pastry-lined pie plate.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Sift 1/2 cup sugar with flour; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Beat shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour milk. Sift together the flour, soda and salt; stir in.
Mix in nuts, cherries and dates.
Chill.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Stir milk into rice; add sugar, salt and eggs, slightly beaten.
Bake in a buttered shallow dish.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Add gelatine to milk in a small pan.
Heat and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Beat 2 egg yolks well with 1 cup of sugar. Whip the cream until stiff.
Beat 2 egg whites and add to yolks and sugar.
Now add gelatine mixture and pour all of this into whipped cream and beat well, adding vanilla.
Put in refrigerator.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, sour cream, milk, soup and 1/2 cheese. Save other half for top. Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: green stuff
directions: Clean and separate broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss.

title: easy lasagna(no precooking of pasta)
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and seasoning.
Simmer 7 minutes.

title: rosemary walnuts
directions: Put walnuts on a cookie sheet.
Mix melted oleo, crushed rosemary, salt and cayenne pepper.
Pour over walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: frosted walnuts
directions: Mix the buttermilk and sugar in a sauce pan and cook slowly until at soft ball stage (approximately 15 minutes).
Take off heat and add the vanilla, stir.
Next add nuts and stir until covered.
Spread onto waxed paper and let cool.
Break apart with fork and store in tin.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to the sugar-egg mixture, blend well.
Add 1/2 cup candy.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; decorate tops with remaining candies.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: okra and shrimp stew
directions: In skillet, begin frying okra, then add all remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour.

title: yum yum delight
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.
Prick holes in the cake with a fork.
Pour juice from one large can of crushed pineapple over cake while it is still hot. Prepare topping.

title: stir-fry veggies and chicken
directions: Chop chicken and veggies; brown chicken in oil first, then add onion and other veggies.
Stir constantly until browned a little. Add soy sauce, garlic and Italian seasoning and a little water. Cover and simmer until you're ready to eat.

title: chicken broccoli fettuccine
directions: Stir margarine and garlic 2 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Add chicken.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Top with fettuccine.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk, water, egg yolks and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into aluminum foil 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Freeze 6 hours or until firm. Scoop ice cream from pan or invert and slice for serving.

title: wild rice and oyster dressing
directions: Measure water into a saucepan and add rice, bouillon granules, margarine and peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer until all water is absorbed (about 25 to 30 minutes).
Add chicken livers that have been chopped in the food processor and the raw oysters.
Cook for about 10 more minutes.
Add green onions.
Stir well and serve.
This dish is relatively expensive to make but it is worth the expense.
The Cobb children think that Christmas and Thanksgiving dinner is incomplete without their wild rice and oyster dressing.
Serves 9.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine Italian dressing, vinegar and curry powder; add to rice mixture and toss well. Cover and chill.

title: butterscotch breakfast rolls(overnight)
directions: Put slices of dough in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pudding and cinnamon.
Mix melted butter, brown sugar and nuts; pour over dough.
Cover with foil and leave on counter overnight.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn over on plate.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking pan; discard bag. Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: s mores
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Heat first 3 ingredients to boiling. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in bowl until coated.
Fold in marshmallows.
Press in pan with buttered spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain grease.
Add chili powder and cumin.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cheeses and blend well.
Add onions, bell peppers and seasonings.
Mix well and chill 1 hour or until firm. Shape into balls.
Roll in finely chopped pecans or walnuts.
This is better served after
it has been allowed to sit 3 to 5 days.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased medium roasting pan and bake for 15 minutes at 325°. Remove from oven and top with caramels melted with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Cover all this with the rest of batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes longer. Top with frosting.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in chocolate.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Peel squash, remove seeds and grate as for cole slaw.
Mix dry ingredients with sugar, eggs and oil.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans, 2 large or 3 small pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Make the Potato Buds for 12.
Add the cream cheese, chives, salt and pepper; mix with Potato Buds.
Add the eggs; beat into mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my mom's mexican casserole(student favorite)
directions: Crush 3/4 bag of Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole (remember to Pam).
Put meat mixture as next layer.
Sprinkle cheese for next layer.
Pour sauce over.
Top with remaining Doritos, which have been left whole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening
and
sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda, add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir
in
vanilla,
coconut
and nuts.
