Mix well.
Fold in
egg whites.
Pour batter in three 8 or 9-inch cake pans
that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: minute cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine pie crust mix, sugar and cinnamon.
Add butter.
Mix until crumbly. Spread pie filling in 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with pie crust mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until light golden brown. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine ingredients in large bowl until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve hot.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes about 60 sausage balls.

title: tossed macaroni
directions: Put Ricotta cheese in serving bowl.
Crumble with a fork.
Add butter and noodles; toss 2 to 3 times.
Cook bacon in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat until crisp.
Add peas and saute 2 minutes; drain fat.
Add bacon and peas to noodles and toss.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss again and serve immediately.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry-banana bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, with electric mixer, combine butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; add flour mixture and bananas alternately to butter mixture, mixing just until ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Fold in dried cherries.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Best served the day after baking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sugar 'n spice cookies
directions: Mix the flour and cinnamon, then add the sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix well, then chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl mix chicken pieces (cooked and cut up in strips), soup, broth and sour cream.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and pour butter over top.
Bake 30 minutes until brown and bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese by letting sit at room temperature. Add Cheddar
cheese
to
cream cheese.
Mix together.
You may add onions,
green
pepper,
chopped
ham, chopped dried beef, pineapple or pecans to your mix.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball over chopped pecans, if desired.

title: beet soup or borsch
directions: Add the sliced beets with juice to the stock with a tablespoon or two of vinegar.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour and water to make a paste and add to the sour cream, stirring or mixing with an eggbeater.

The trick to not getting lumpy sour cream in soup is to add some hot soup (not boiling) to the flour mixture, a ladle at a time, stirring or mixing as you do this, for 6 or 7 ladles. Add this mixture to the pot of soup, stirring while adding.
Make sure the soup is not boiling.
If soup is still too sweet, add another tablespoon or two of vinegar or dill pickle juice.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil; mix well. Add eggs and beat. Combine all dry ingredients and then add to mixture, alternating with water. Stir in sweet potatoes and nuts. Pour batter into 3 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in a large kettle; cover with water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender. Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl; combine cream cheese, butter and soup.
Stir well.
Add milk and bacon.
Add to vegetables and heat through.
For a thicker soup, drain vegetables before adding cream cheese mixture.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Sprinkle onion powder, garlic powder and salt on cubed chicken breasts to your liking.
Fry until chicken cubes are browned.

title: salmon steaks with dijon sauce
directions: Rub surface of fish with lemon juice.
Place steaks or fillets on foil lined baking dish (or broiler pan) without track.
Cut butter into pea size pieces; dot top of salmon.
Broil 5 minutes. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, mustard and dill or tarragon. Spread on broiled steaks (fillets); do not turn salmon.
Broil an additional 2 to 3 minutes to brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and let cool. Combine all vegetables in a covered bowl; pour cooled vinegar mixture over vegetables and stir well.
Chill several hours before serving. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: cook it quick
directions: Oil grill.
Mix flour, sugar and baking soda well.
Beat egg in a bowl.
Blend in buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Blend in margarine.
If thinner pancake is desired, add 1/4 cup more buttermilk.
Use about 1/4 cup batter per pancake. Put on grill and fry.
Serve immediately.
Good with sausage or bacon.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine in a bowl for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured 10 x 14-inch cake pan.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Drain.
Cook creamed spinach (follow package directions.)
Empty spinach pouches into large bowl and cool.
Stir in Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella, salt and pepper.
Stuff each shell with tablespoon of cheese mixture.
In skillet, cook ground beef.
Stir in jar of spaghetti sauce.
Put stuffed shells in casserole and pour sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on cookie sheet. Bake until done.
Cool.

title: pizza
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add remaining water, oil and salt in big bowl.
Gradually stir in flour one cup at a time until dough forms a ball and pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on a floured surface; knead 10 minutes.
Return to oiled bowl; cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down; divide in 2 parts.
Roll out flat on floured surface. Sprinkle 2 cookie sheets with cornmeal.
Spread out each dough on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle each with equal amounts of sauce, cheese, oregano and favorite toppings.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: frances phillip's broccoli casserole
directions: Partially cook broccoli in salt water and drain.
Mix soup, onion and mayonnaise.
Layer broccoli, soup mixture and cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers and pour melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: coconut-sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake; cool and split layers.
Blend sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers.
Combine reserved sour cream with whipped topping.
Spread on top and sides of cake. Seal cake in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: walnut crescents
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Gradually blend in flour.
Stir in nuts. Shape a spoonful of dough into rolls about 3 inches long.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Pull ends down to form a crescent. Bake at 350° for 15 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly on pan.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Dip ends in chocolate glaze and then in jimmies or coconut.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat well the first 6 ingredients.
Add the vinegar and a little celery seed.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: pork chop sauce
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Bring sauce to boil; simmer for 15 minutes.
Put on chops to charbroil on grill.
Freeze sauce over and over.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix greens and dressing.
Place croutons on top.

title: 24-hour vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, place 3 cups of torn lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer eggs over lettuce.
Sprinkle with salt. Next, layer in order the green peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread
mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with sliced green onions and paprika, if desired.
Toss gently before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add rest of ingredients and bake until done.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Bring 6 ounces of Coke to a boil.
Pour over cherry jello. Add the rest of the Coke and mix well.
Add pineapple.
Add pecans.
Mix well; refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: paprika chicken
directions: *If using a pressure cooker use 1 teaspoon paprika, 3 tablespoons flour, 4 tablespoons fat, 1 bouillon cube and 1 1/2 cups water.

title: sangria
directions: Pour lemon and orange juice into large pitcher.
Add sugar; stir to blend.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill in fridge.
To serve, pour into wide wine glasses; place some fruit in each glass.
Can be made well in advance.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Saute garlic in oil over low flame for 5 minutes.
Discard garlic.
Brown cutlets in oil.
Mix flour, pepper and nutmeg; sprinkle over brown meat.
Add onion and wine.
Cover skillet and simmer about 20 minutes, turning meat several times.
Add more liquid (wine or tomato juice) if necessary.
Add mushrooms; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve on a warm platter with sauce, garnished with paprika and parsley.
Yield:
4 servings. Approximate calories/serving:

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and dry jello together in large bowl.
Chill.

title: snow-day apple pancake
directions: Set the oven at 400°.
Heat a 9-inch cast-iron skillet or other heavy-duty ovenproof skillet.
Melt the butter.
Combine the cinnamon and sugar.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the mixture over the apples and saute them until tender over low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: cottage cheese delight
directions: Mix together and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve in pretty salad bowl.

title: bubble brew
directions: Gently stir all ingredients together in a big plastic container.

title: peach salad
directions: Cut drained peaches into tiny pieces (or put drained peaches in blender for a few seconds).
Sprinkle jello over peaches and stir; let set for just a minute or two.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve.

title: herb tea blend
directions: Combine all ingredients in a resealable plastic bag.

title: date nut fingers
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar, eggs, dates and nuts.
Bring to a boil; continue cooking at a slow boil for 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour mixture over Rice Krispies.
Shape into logs or balls and roll in coconut.
Store in sealed container in refrigerator.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sesame shrimp and asparagus
directions: Trim asparagus and cut into 2 inch pieces.
In wok or large skillet toast sesame seed until golden; set aside.
In same skillet over medium-high heat oil, add asparagus, onions and shrimp.
Cook until tender and crisp, stirring frequently for 5 minutes.
Stir in sesame seed, soy sauce and salt.
Just mix and stir.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate sugar puffs
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add chocolate which has been melted.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in 4x sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: rice with grilled pork medallions
directions: Cook onion and celery in olive oil in a large saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add chicken broth and dried thyme; bring mixture to a boil.
Rinse wild rice in 3 changes of hot water; drain.
Add wild rice to broth mixture. Cover.
Reduce heat and cook 30 minutes.
Add black-eyed peas and next 7 ingredients; cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serve with grilled pork medallions and apple wedges. Garnish, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; let set overnight.
Then add pineapple, marshmallows, pecans and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all in bowl and chill.

title: butterfinger peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir in crushed candy bars and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: carilou's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat eggs and add to sugar and oil mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and form a ball. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll dough as thin as you like.
Pinch a small portion of dough and form a ball in your hand.
Flatten the small ball of dough and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: delicious casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, celery and onion lightly and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: too easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into eggs, then into bread crumbs to coat thoroughly.
In large skillet, place chicken in hot oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.
Pour 1 cup sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer chicken and top with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until thoroughly cooked.
Serves 8.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into three greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges. Bake in 3 well-greased round cake pan or one 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and spread with icing.

title: cool rise cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
Add oleo, hot water and eggs.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes at medium speed. Gradually add remaining flour until it pulls away from sides of bowl.
Remove and knead until elastic.
Cover with plastic and towel and let rest 20 minutes.
Punch down and divide in half. Roll out and spread with oleo, brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Roll into jelly roll and slice 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place in jelly roll pan.
Brush lightly with oil. Cover with plastic wrap and let rise in refrigerator overnight.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix butter, oatmeal, flour and brown sugar until crumbly. Place half in bottom of 8-inch pan.

title: hands off biscuits
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1-quart freezer bag.
Close bag; mix ingredients.
Open bag occasionally to expel air.
When mixed thoroughly, snip one bottom corner with scissors about 1 inch. Squeeze dough on baking pan.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
Sprinkle tops with flour; pat down to desired thickness with fork.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes at 425°, or until brown.

title: creamy honey dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix very well and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Combine olive oil, onion and garlic in a large skillet.
Add all vegetables and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook on medium-high heat (stirring occasionally) until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.
Serve over cooked pasta. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach; salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter.
Add flour and eggs and mix everything.
Put into 9 x 12-inch dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until cheese turns slightly brown on top.
Serves 12.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in glass jar.
Add mixture to water to taste and serve with ice.

title: delicious pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Stir in pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into pumpkin mixture.
Add water and nuts (optional), mixing well.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: petticoat tails
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flavoring until very creamy.
Sift flour and salt together, then mix all the ingredients until the dough is like modeling clay (the dough is not sticky).
Roll in waxed paper or put into fruit juice cans.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Slice thin and bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: smoky broiled fish
directions: Brush inside of fish with mixed ingredients.
Place in greased pan.
Brush fish with sauce.
Broil for awhile, then turn.
Brush with sauce.
Continue to broil until done at 325°.

title: quick brownies
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Melt together over low heat the cocoa and margarine.
Remove
from
heat, add sugar, flour and eggs. Mix well
and
pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with
nuts.
Bake
to 30 minutes. Center will be firm and moist.
Cut into squares, about 20.

title: apple crescent snacks
directions: Wash, peel and core apple.
Chop apple into small pieces. Measure sugar and cinnamon; combine in a small bowl (add nutmeg, if desired).

title: oven beef burgundy
directions: Shake meat with flour, salt and pepper in a plastic bag to coat well.
Reserve any remaining flour mixture.
Brown beef, part at a time, in hot butter in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Lift out beef as it browns and transfer it to a 2 1/4 to 3-quart baking dish.
Heat brandy in a small pan.
Ignite.
Pour over beef.
Add onions and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with any reserved flour mixture. Stir garlic, parsley and thyme into fat remaining in skillet.
Cook 1 minute.
Add beef broth and wine.
Heat, stirring to loosen browned bits, until mixture comes to boiling.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Add bay leaf.
Cover.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple butter cookies
directions: Cream together butter, margarine or peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix together well.
Dough should be stiff.
Roll into 1-inch balls and flatten with fork tines on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until lightly brown around the edges only.

title: hot lettuce salad
directions: Toss dressing with lettuce (or spinach) and eggs just before serving.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Melt chocolate and add to melted shortening.
Add sugar, egg, milk and vanilla, then add sifted dry ingredients.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet and bake in 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, water and vanilla, blending until smooth.
Quickly stir in chocolate and nuts.
Turn into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan, spreading 1 inch thick.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: snack time favorite cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars and beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts, crushed Wheaties and oats.
Mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cabbage fry
directions: Place oil/butter in skillet; put cabbage, green pepper and onion in skillet.
Place sliced Polish sausage on top and let simmer until cabbage is tender.
Season to taste.
Best served with cornbread.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, adding the milk last, while mixing to the desired texture.
Pour onto hot griddle.
Cook and enjoy!

title: stir and drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with a fork until well blended. Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg and stir into oil mixture.
Drop with teaspoon 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten with greased glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes to a delicate brown.
Remove immediately from baking sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: million dollar relish
directions: Soak cucumbers (covered with water) and salt for 3 hours. Rinse and drain.
Chop cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Seal in pint jars which have been sterilized.
Great on hot dogs and in salads.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into strips and layer in 9 x 13-inch pan over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice together and pour over chicken.
Put crumbs in melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: johnny appleseed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan melt margarine over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend in remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch square or 11 x 17-inch pan, greased bottom only.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched in center.
Serve warm or cool, plain or with whipped cream or frosting.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, pineapple and nuts.
Spray a 2-quart casserole with Pam or oil with margarine.
Alternate layers of sweet potato mixture and marshmallows, ending with marshmallows. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Will serve 10 to 12.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water 10 to 15 minutes; drain and rinse in cold water. Place in icebox to cool for 10 minutes. Add in the rest of the ingredients, draining tuna fish first; mix well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add vanilla; stir in zucchini. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Stir into first mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, instant jello and sugar. Add whip cream to soften and sugar to taste.
Prepare pudding according to instructions. Layer cream cheese mix on bottom and pudding on top. Top with chocolate or strawberries as desired.
Place in freezer for 45 minutes to allow to set.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Add 1 cup water to zucchini.
Bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes.
Add next 3 ingredients and cook 6 minutes more.
Add jello and stirring, continue to cook until it is dissolved.
Also stir jam while it is cooking.
You can use other flavors of jello. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: sally lunn bread(from williamsburg)
directions: Scald the milk or bring it almost to a simmer and add the butter, sugar and salt.
Let cool until tepid (95°).
Dissolve the yeast in 1/4 cup
of tepid water.
Using your electric mixer, if you have a powerful one, beat the eggs and then add the milk mixture, then yeast water and finally the flour.
Beat until smooth, about 5 minutes.

title: double decker fudge
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with aluminum foil.
Place 1 cup peanut butter chips in medium bowl; set aside.
In second medium bowl, stir together cocoa, melted butter and vanilla until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining 1 cup chips; set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan stir together sugar, Marshmallow Creme, evaporated milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Immediately add half of hot mixture to bowl with peanut butter chips only.
Pour remainder into cocoa mixture; stir to blend.
Beat peanut butter mixture until chips are completely melted.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Beat cocoa mixture until chips are melted and mixture thickens.
Spread evenly over top of peanut butter layer.
Cool until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil.
Cut into squares.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place.

title: berry bananas
directions: Slice the bananas.
Wash and clean the berries.
Layer the banana slices and berries in a dish.
If desired, add yogurt or milk and sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: *Can use self-rising flour, but eliminate salt, baking powder and soda.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix above ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until cool.

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: In a bowl, mix together the onion, potatoes, beans and turkey. Add dressing to moisten the mixture, then add more dressing, if desired.
Garnish with sprinkling of fresh parsley and a dash of paprika.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken with enough water to cover, until done. Remove chicken, reserve broth. After cooling, remove meat from bones and chop meat. Cook noodles in reserved broth according to package directions. Melt butter in large pan; add green peppers, onions and mushrooms. Saut until soft. Add all ingredients to noodles, stirring until Velveeta melts. Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles, add American cheese to top of casserole, bake until cheese melts. This dish freezes well for potlucks, etc.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and lay margarine sticks on top.
Do not stir.
Cook on High for 6 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into buttered platter. Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.
Do not double this recipe.

title: lillie's layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients and spread mayonnaise over the top. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Seal and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; beat cheese and gradually add gelatin.
Beat well.
Stir in pineapple and baby food; fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and chill.
Cut into squares and place on lettuce leaves.

title: yogurt salad
directions: Chop apples. Peel and chop oranges. Place equal portions of chopped fruit into 4 small bowls. Top each with 1/2 cup yogurt and sprinkle with pecans.

title: sausage barbecue
directions: Fry sausage; drain grease off.
Add soup, sauce, paste and mushrooms.
Let simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Place cabbage, onion and mango in a bowl.
In saucepan, bring vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed to a boil.
Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, then pour over salad mixture and toss.
Refrigerate overnight or longer.
The longer it sets, the better.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender; blend well.
Pour ingredients in greased souffle dish. Place souffle dish in a pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: frozen tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan; cook until soft.
Let cool, then puree mixture in a blender.
Bag and freeze.

title: crystallized ginger pickles(mrs. buddy quin)
directions: Use overgrown cucumbers that yellow.
Soak cucumbers in lime 24 hours.
Wash.
Soak in
alum
water 24 hours and wash. Soak in ginger water 24 hours.
Do	not wash unless too strong with ginger.
Just drain
well.	Combine vinegar, water, sugar and pickling spice.
Soak cucumbers
in
the solution 4 hours. Then boil 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Can be used over many vegetables, casseroles and baked potatoes.
Heat slightly before spooning over baked potatoes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in ungreased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Blend on low speed until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press in the bottom of prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle immediately with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes, then spread evenly.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and fill cupcake papers, with cookie on bottom, about 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 14 minutes.
Top with cherries.

title: marinated steak
directions: Prepare meat with tenderizer as directed on bottle.
Combine with all other ingredients in shallow pan or plastic bag.
Add meat and marinate in refrigerator for 6 to 12 hours or overnight. Place steak on grill 6 inches above hot coals.
Grill 12 to 25 minutes, basting occasionally, turn over, continue basting and grilling 10 to 15 minutes for medium.
Makes a cheaper cut of meat tasty and tender.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer in casserole dish (approximately 9 x 13-inch).
Heat in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve with chips. Quick and easy!

title: ham-potato-pineapple bake
directions: Trim excess fat from ham.
Place in an 11 x 7 x 1/2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Arrange potatoes and pineapple over ham; set aside.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until hot. Pour over ham.
Cover; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yields servings for 4.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar with oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time,
beating
after
each.
Sift
dry
ingredients.
Add alternately with
milk
and vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: In a large bowl whisk together oil and dressing mix.
Pour over crackers; toss lightly to coat.
Spread crackers onto a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes, stirring after 7 minutes.
Makes 6 cups.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Measure flour by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll up teaspoonfuls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together and serve with 7-up or Sprite. Can be frozen.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot. Cook until broccoli becomes tender, about 3 hours.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Spoon flour into dry measuring cup; level off and pour measured flour onto waxed paper.
Add flour (not sifted).
Stir to blend.
Cream peanut butter, sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Mix until smooth.
Stir in chocolate bits and peanuts.

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk, orange rind, orange juice and oil, mixing well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
(Do not overmix.)
Stir in raisins or dates. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes one dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Place in large casserole dish.
Crush corn flakes; place on top.
Pour melted butter on top of corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix butter, 1/2 cup of sugar and flour until crumbly.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Place apples, mixed with 1/2 cup of sugar, in pan and top with crumb mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: el rancho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 8-inch round cake pan with nonstick spray.
Unroll dough; form 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Place in sprayed pan with dough extending evenly over sides of pan. Press dough in bottom and up sides of pan. Sprinkle 1 cup cheese over dough.
Spread pizza sauce over cheese.
Top with pepperoni and remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cut 2-inch cut at each corner of dough.
Bring all ends at
center together.
Twist to secure at top of pizza.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oven roasted "new" potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash and cut potatoes if large.
Put potatoes in a 13 x 9-inch shallow dish.
Add next 3 ingredients; toss to coat.
Bake 35 minutes, shaking pan twice or stirring until potatoes are lightly browned.
Sprinkle with chives or parsley. Contains 3 g fat.

title: crock-pot calico beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer on low heat in crock-pot all day.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add all other ingredients one at a time mixing well after each.
Bake at 350° in loaf pans.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add eggs and buttermilk.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Bake at
350°	for 45 minutes or until set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Add flour and cream of tartar to remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken salad finger sandwiches
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, tossing well. Stir in mayonnaise; cover and chill.

title: grape pie
directions: Make pastry for a two-crust 9-inch pie; line pie pan with one crust.
Remove and save skins from the grapes.
Put pulp into a saucepan without water; bring to a rolling boil.
While hot, rub through strainer to remove seeds.
Mix strained pulp with skins. Mix lightly through grapes the sugar and flour.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt.
Pour grapes into pastry lined pie pan; dot with the butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it. Bake until crust is nicely browned and juice begins to bubble, at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve cool or slightly warm, not hot.

title: frozen pudding sandwiches
directions: Gradually add milk to peanut butter in bowl, blending until smooth.
add pudding mix.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes. Can also use hand whisk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread filling about 1/2-inch thick on 12 of the graham cracker squares.
Top with remaining squares, pressing lightly and smoothing around edges with spatula.
Freeze until firm, about 3 hours.
Sandwiches can be stored, wrapped, in freezer 3 to 4 days.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots and combine all ingredients.
Chill.

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine soups and milk; stir in boned chicken.
Add noodles and mix.
Bake in a greased 2-quart oblong casserole dish for 20 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: greek walnut cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together. Beat eggs well; add sugar. Add flour and liquids, alternately, to egg mixture, mixing thoroughly after each addition. Add walnuts; mix thoroughly. Stir baking soda into the cognac; mix it into batter. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake approximately 45 minutes in 400° oven. As soon as cake is baked, remove from oven and cut into squares. Pour warm honey into all lines and around edges of warm cake. Grate walnuts over cake.

title: moo goo gai pan(chinese chicken and mushrooms)
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts.
Slice across breasts into 1/8-inch slices.
In a medium bowl mix chicken, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, ginger, sugar and garlic powder.
Set aside.
Thinly slice mushrooms.
Cut each green onion crosswise into 3-inch pieces.
In a 12-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat in 1/4 cup hot salad oil, cook mushrooms and green onions, stirring quickly and frequently until mushrooms are tender (about 2 minutes).

With a slotted spoon, remove mushroom mixture to bowl. In same skillet or wok, over high heat, in 3 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook chicken mixture, stirring frequently and quickly, until chicken is tender (about 2 or 3 minutes).
Return mushroom mixture to skillet and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: fuzzy navel punch
directions: Combine orange juice, peach Schnapps and champagne.
Pour into punch bowl; add crushed ice or frozen ice ring.
Yields 1 gallon of punch.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Layer tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: london broil
directions: Preheat broiler.
With sharp knife, score both sides of flank steak for even broiling.
Place steak in broiling pan.
In bowl, mix onions, olive oil and salt.
Rub mixture on both sides of steak.

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and toss gently to coat.
Turn into a baking dish.
Blend dry topping ingredients and cut in margarine to make crumbs.
Spread on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Good served with ice milk, vanilla yogurt or whipped topping.

title: cabbage and potatoes
directions: Wash and separate cabbage.
Wash and peel potatoes.
Slice very thin.
Slice onion.
In large pot, add all ingredients and cook over low heat until potatoes are done.
Serve with corned beef.

title: tangy sachet
directions: Mix together mint, orange peel and cloves.
Divide in half. Take 2 pieces of material, placing the wrong sides together.
Sew 3 sides together.
Fill with half the mixture.
Makes great gifts.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix together. Roll in small balls, place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees.

title: sesame-cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle seed evenly on bottoms and sides of greased 2-quart casserole.
Beat egg in large bowl on low speed, then add remaining ingredients and beat on medium speed 30 seconds.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes. Immediately invert and remove from casserole.
Great cubed for fondue or other dipping.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, celery and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste, then drain.
Place half of vegetables in dish, half of cheese and half of mayonnaise.
Start over with rest of vegetables, cheese and mayonnaise.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs mixed with butter. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix the ingredients and form into balls a little larger than a walnuts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze meat and cut meat into strips 3 inches long and 1/4-inch wide.
In large skillet, brown meat strips in hot Crisco; drain off excess fat.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid. Add reserved liquid, the water, onion, garlic, salt and pepper to meat in skillet.
Cover and simmer 60 minutes or until meat is tender.
Uncover and put in Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in the water and flour mixture; cook until thickened and bubbly.
Cut the green peppers in 2-inch long strips; add to meat along with the drained tomatoes which have been cut up.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german chocolate apple pie cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs and pie filling 5 to 8 minutes.
Pour in prepared 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients except oil and stir into dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown turning once.
Drain on paper towels and serve warm.
Makes twelve 2-inch fritters.

title: time-to-spare-ribs
directions: You will need 1 large 14 x 20 Reynolds cooking bag.

title: mildred's oyster stew
directions: Heat the milk and cream in a pot.
Do not boil.
Add oysters and any oyster juice.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Season to taste. Add butter. Heat until it melts and serve very hot.

title: ed harmon's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water.
Add salt, sugar and vegetable oil and mix together.
Add eggs and 3 cups flour; mix.
Add 1 more cup flour and knead.
(May need to add a little flour if sticky.) Let rise; knead again into rolls or bread.
Use a greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top. Rub butter on top of each roll.
This is a good recipe to use for cinnamon rolls/bread.

title: doctor janice's doodle mix
directions: Melt 2 pounds white almond bark and stir in above mix.
Spread immediately onto wax paper.
Break apart when cooled.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and broccoli in microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Set aside.
Blend cottage cheese in blender or food processor until very smooth; slowly add milk while continuing to blend.
Add chicken soup to cheese/milk mixture.
Blend; add mixture to cooked, undrained vegetables. Microwave until heated thoroughly (about 3 minutes) without boiling.
Add salt and pepper.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: cherry macaroon parfaits
directions: Prepare pudding with milk as directed on package.
Combine cherry filling and extract.
Alternate layers of pudding, crumbled cookies and filling in 6 parfait or dessert dishes.
Garnish with topping.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation time is 10 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: You can also use firm ripe tomatoes.
Select firm, ripe tomatoes or firm green tomatoes.
Wash them and cut in 1/2-inch slices without removing the skins.
Dip each slice in bread crumbs or flour; saute in hot oil or Crisco.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: brownie cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Cool, stirring occasionally while cooling.
Stir in dry cake mix and stir well.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chip bits and nuts. Bake as directed on package.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: cottage meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine ketchup, tomato juice, salt and pepper, eggs, bread crumbs, onions and mustard.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Add ground beef.
Mix gently but thoroughly. Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
Press in the beef mixture.

title: aunt florie's oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the oatmeal in a medium bowl.
Pour boiling water on the oatmeal and let stand while preparing the rest of the ingredients.
Cream butter and sugars (brown and granulated) until fluffy.
Sift the dry ingredients (flour and cinnamon), then add them to the butter and sugar mixture.
Pour in the vanilla and the oatmeal.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) layer pans or one 12 x 9 x 2-inch utility pan.
Bake in the oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together into a 3-quart glass casserole.
Add milk; mix until partially blended.
Place margarine over top.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add pecans; mix well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered dish.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: bisquick chicken pie
directions: Take chicken off bone and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add soup and broth, pour over chicken. Mix Bisquick and milk; pour over chicken. Cut up margarine and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown together onion, green pepper, hamburger and rice.
Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce, water and mustard.
Bring mixture to a boil, then simmer for 25 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: After heating, pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Boil the water out of the green beans.
Place in a casserole dish and pour the mushroom soup over beans (add 1/4 cup water to can of soup).
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Place onion rings on top and brown.

title: ruth's frozen fruit salad
directions: In large bowl combine milk and pie filling.
Add the mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple; add nuts.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Place rice and corn in layers in a 2-quart baking dish. Season to taste.
Pour 1 can of tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water over the layers.
Add layers of the onion and green pepper.
Cover with a layer of seasoned meat.
Pour remaining can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can of water over casserole.
Top with bacon strips. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings.

title: consomme rice(brown rice)
directions: Dice onions and celery in small pieces.
Melt oleo (margarine) in a large pot.
Saute onions and celery.
Combine French onion soup, beef consomme soup and sliced mushrooms with sauteed onions and celery.
Rinse rice and add to ingredients.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered. Stir every 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: gourmet olives
directions: Drain olives and transfer to large jar.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over olives.
Cover and refrigerate 10 to 12 hours; shake olives occasionally to coat evenly.
Olives can be stored in refrigerator no longer than 2 weeks.
Drain well before serving.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together. Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
Place chicken in deep baking dish (3 or 4-inch).

title: marinated slaw
directions: Shred cabbage in a large bowl.
Place chopped onion and green pepper on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar evenly on top.
Bring oil, vinegar, mustard, celery seed and salt to a boil.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Don't stir.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 4 hours (better if refrigerated overnight).
Stir mixture and drain before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook butter, water and chopped broccoli for 3 minutes, remove pan from heat, then add Velveeta and Minute rice.
Cover pan and let set for 4 minutes.
Add cream of celery soup.

title: fresh ham with sherry sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Roast 40 minutes per pound.
With a sharp knife, cut 10 or more one-inch deep holes in top surface of ham; press garlic slivers and pinch of black pepper in each hole. Place roast on rack in open pan.
Rub surface with sherry and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Roast 40 minutes per pound or until meat thermometer is 185°.
Pour off fat and combine with 2/3 cup sherry; thicken with cornstarch for sauce.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Slightly mix ingredients together.

title: fluffy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping.
Mix with 1 cup of milk as directed on package in small mixer bowl.
Measure 2 cups of the prepared whipped topping and set aside.
Add 1 cup milk and chocolate pudding mix to remaining topping in bowl.
Blend and then beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: enchiladas(joe and sonya kuykendall, 11-3-78)
directions: Put can of tomato sauce and enchilada mix in pan and mix. Heat over low fire.
Brown beef and onion over low fire in skillet.
After sauce heats 10 minutes, add to the beef, just enough to be slightly soupy (to your preference).

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Wash, split and remove stems from peppers; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine vinegar, water and oil; bring to a boil. Drop in peppers, onion and carrot slices; cook just long enough for peppers to change color.
Place peppers and vegetables into pint jars to which 1/2 teaspoon of salt, 1 garlic clove and 1 bay leaf have been added to each.
Distribute liquid into jars.
Seal.

title: warm brie salad with hazelnut vinaigrette(4 persons)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place hazelnuts on a baking sheet and bake for 20 minutes.
Cool and rub in a dish towel to remove the skin.
Chop the hazelnuts finely and set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with onions.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and eggs.
Stir into broccoli.
Add cheese; mix well.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Add cheese, then crackers on top as crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add taco seasoning, beans and tomato sauce and simmer five minutes.
Press dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan and up the sides one inch.
Brush on oil and sprinkle corn meal over dough.
Pour meat sauce over dough and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes and cook until melted.
Cut into cubes.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, taco sauce and sour cream.

title: seafood souffle
directions: Line bread on the bottom of a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Combine the next 9 ingredients and pour on top. Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Let sit 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: happy days
directions: Take all of the ingredients and add a pinch of warm personality and a dash of humor.
Measure the words carefully, the heaping amount of time and patience.
Keep temperature low.
Do not boil.
Add a dash of humor and a pinch of warm spice of life. Serve to individuals garnished with a big smile.

title: peach fruit salad
directions: Whip together the milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Fold in pie filling, pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate.

title: peachy dessert off the grill
directions: Cut bananas and peaches into bite size pieces.
Place fruit in a foil pan or make your own pan with heavy duty foil.
In a bowl, stir together honey, butter and 1/2 tsp. cinnamon.
Spoon over fruit and toss to coat fruit.

title: rich's irish creme
directions: Combine all ingredients in jug or container; shake vigorously.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for one hour.
Make small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: "steak-on-a-stick over an open scaly-bark fire"
directions: You will need 3 sticks (1 healthy and long, 2 in shape of a "Y") and scaly-bark fire.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large pan, melt margarine.
Add flour and make a roux. Stir and add chicken broth and 1 can cream of chicken soup (add water, broth or milk if this is too thick).
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour in 9 x 13 pan.
Put uncooked biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and celery.
In a separate bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Add chicken and celery.
Let chill for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook and stir in hot oil 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce; add to pan.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to boil and turn down to simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and margarine. Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over cut up rhubarb in 9-inch pastry lined pie pan. Top with pastry cut fancy shapes or just bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla. Mix well until eggs are cooked in hot rice. Add milk and raisins. Return to low heat, stirring continuously for about 5 minutes.
Pour into serving dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and brown sugar.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Heat the oil; add dry salad dressing.
Mix dill weed and garlic salt.
Mix and pour over the oyster crackers.
Stir with a wooden spoon.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix in bowl by hand.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: gumbo
directions: In a pot (not iron), saut okra, onions, celery and garlic until done or all the stringiness is gone from the okra.

title: pie crusts
directions: Mix
flour,
salt and Crisco until fine like meal.
Add water, egg and vinegar.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and pineapple juice. Beat until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in coconut, drained pineapple and oranges.
Pour into chilled cookie crust.
Chill until firm.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cut chicken into small pieces and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 11 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel, crumble and set aside.
Cook green onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, dry mustard, paprika and pepper.
Blend well.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly stirring constantly.
Beat eggs in small bowl, stir in milk.
Gradually add to flour mixture.
Cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir in corn.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: sharon's cinnamon christmas cut-outs
directions: Mix together; roll out using cinnamon for dusting.
Cut out with
cookie
cutters.
Let dry on cookie sheet for 3 to 4 days. Poke hole in top with toothpick and/or decorate.
These make your house
smell really nice.
You can paint on them or stencil
after they
are
dry.
Probably
frosting would work also.

title: english rose cherry whip
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in water.
Chill until slightly set, then whip.
Add pineapple, drained well.
Pour into pan greased well with oleo and lined with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: outrageous blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use liners or grease and flour pans.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until it easily comes off the bone.
Mix flour and shortening well; add beaten egg and milk.
Roll onto floured surface, about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Put chicken meat back into the dumplings and broth. Cover and cook until dumplings are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together milk, egg yolks and lime juice.
Beat 1 egg white stiff and fold into mixture. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat 3 egg whites and gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Spread over filling and bake at 350° until egg whites are golden brown.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, egg, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Add flour, soda and salt. Cover dough and chill until firm (1 hour). Make into walnut size balls and place in greased mini muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes. Press a peanut butter cup in each and let cool in pan.

title: pretzels
directions: Put pretzels in cake pan.
Break pretzels into smaller pieces. Mix all the mixture together, then pour over pretzels.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix about three times while it is baking.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar and salt; blend well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with your favorite pastry recipe.
(The secret of the crust is not to have it too thin.
It should be thick so the custard won't run through.)
Brush the pastry with melted butter, pour custard into pastry shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Combine flour, salt and paprika; coat chicken well.
Melt butter; brown chicken on both sides.
Remove from pan; place into casserole dish.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Combine chicken soup with 1 can water; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend together eggs and sugar until light and well blended. Add oil and continue to beat.
Sift and stir dry ingredients together and thoroughly beat into egg mixture.
Add pumpkin and mix well again.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Do not add salt.

title: cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill dough for 3 hours. Roll out on floured table for cutouts.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool before icing.

title: divinity
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and water.
Cook to hard ball stage (260°) stirring only until sugar is dissolved.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites to a stiff peak. Gradually pour syrup over egg whites beating at high speed on electric mixer.
Add vanilla and beat until candy holds its shape in 4 to 5 minutes.
Quickly drop from teaspoon onto wax paper. Makes about 40 pieces.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Layer the following in casserole dish:

title: cranberry delight
directions: Beat cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk. Beat in cranberry sauce and nuts. Chill for 45-60 min. Use as a dessert or late night snack. Makes 8-10 servings.

title: donna's low-fat chili
directions: Brown turkey in skillet.
Drain off any fat.
You may even wash over turkey with water if you wish.
Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on low all day or all night.
You can soak pintos in water all night first before putting into crock-pot. This will make pintos softer.
Be sure to add enough water so chili does not dry out.
Great for low-fat nachos.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Add soups and sour cream.
Pour melted butter on top.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Cook until cracker crumbs are brown at 425°.

title: dipped chocolate candy
directions: Work all but last
two
ingredients
together
and make into balls (for Easter I make
mine the shape of Easter eggs). Melt chocolate chips and 1/2
block paraffin in double boiler. Dip candy, using toothpick, ice pick
or two tine fork.
Drain and put on wax paper.
I find it works better to make my candy at night and dip it in the morning.

title: oven barbecue country spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in oil for 20 minutes.
Add cut up green pepper, sliced onion rings and cut up celery to pan drippings (remove ribs before to baking dish).
Mix tomato sauce, paste and water; add to sauteed vegetables.
When hot, pour over ribs.
Cover with foil. Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: baked beans 'n meat
directions: Heat in crock-pot for 2 hours.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar until blended.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape scant teaspoon of dough into balls.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top each cookie with Kiss, pressing down until cookie cracks.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: pull apart cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Layer pecans and dinner rolls. Combine sugar, cinnamon and pudding. Sprinkle over top of rolls. Melt butter and pour over everything. Cover with a towel and let stand overnight. In AM, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add in order, corn oil, egg yolks, water, lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until egg whites form very stiff peaks.
Fold first mixture into egg whites until well blended.
Do not stir.
Turn batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 to 75 minutes.
Invert pan and cool.
Loosen sides with spatula.

title: popovers
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Gradually add milk to flour in a small bowl.
Add butter.
Beat eggs well and add to batter. Beat batter for 2 minutes with mixer.
Fill hot muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in a 450° oven for 14 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 more minutes.
Serve hot.
They can be filled with creamed vegetables or creamed meat.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles.
Place 1/2 noodles on bottom of casserole.
Add ingredients and top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream margarine and vegetable oil.
Add sugar and eggs. Combine flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in maple flavoring.
Add coconut and nuts.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cherries and nuts.
Form into 2 rolls (each 2 inches in diameter and 8 inches long).
Roll in coconut. Wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: meat loaf with cheese
directions: Combine meat with next	8
ingredients.
Place	half of this mixture in a loaf pan.
Cover with half of cheese and top with half of the
parsley.
Repeat
with
the
remaining meat, cheese and parsley.
Bake at 350°	for
1	hour or until done. Sprinkle with paprika and let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jello and sugar in hot water.
Add pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate.
Add sour cream and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine oil, egg and buttermilk.
Stir in flour mixture.
Cut frankfurters into 5 pieces.
Dip each piece into batter.
Coat completely.
Use wooden picks to aid in dipping.
Pour oil 3 to 4-inches deep in Dutch oven or pan.
Heat to 375°.
Fry until golden brown.
Turn once while frying.
Serve with mustard and ketchup.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese in margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix in a blender; cool.
Pour into greased 12 x 9-inch cake pan. Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13 pan, layer chicken on bottom, onions and Doritos (crushed). Mix cream of chicken and Ro-Tel together. Pour soup mixture over Doritos. Slowly pour chicken broth over soup mixture. Cover with cheese. Cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven. Carefully remove foil. Bake additional 15 to 25 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Turn ingredients into shallow buttered casserole dish.
Combine cheese and chips; spread over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: less-than-an-hour vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground meat, draining away as much grease as possible; add chopped onion and brown with meat.
Add seasonings and undrained tomatoes.
Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Chop carrots and celery finely.
Simmer 45 minutes or more, according to size of vegetable pieces.
Serves 4 meals.
It freezes perfectly.

title: one dish pork chop dinner
directions: Coat pork chops in flour; reserve excess flour. In a large Dutch oven, heat oil.
Brown pork on both sides. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove and set aside.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion with salt and garlic; drain. Put into bottom of casserole dish. Add cooked potatoes, then Cheddar cheese. Top with soup and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 20 minutes at 300°.
Sprinkle cheese on top to melt.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: Lay chipped beef on bottom of pan.
Wrap bacon around chicken breasts.
Mix sour cream and chicken soup; pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: fried venison backstrap
directions: Mix flour and milk in medium sized bowl with whisk until all lumps are out.
Add spices and mix well.

title: mother's icebox sugarless cake
directions: In large saucepan, heat milk and marshmallows, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted.
Add in all the other ingredients and place in bowl or pan that has been lined with waxed paper and lightly greased with softened margarine.
Cover, refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator the next day and remove from bowl, discarding the waxed paper.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and keep in refrigerator or freezer until time to eat.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water until tender.
Mash eggplant and combine with next 7 ingredients.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: herbed spinach bake(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Cut into squares.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Toss chicken in bowl with mixture of soy sauce, rice wine and cornstarch; set aside.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice and let stand until almost jelled.
Combine cranberry-orange relish, chopped apple and pecans. Fold into the almost jelled mixture. Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 small servings.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Tenderize onion in stick of oleo.
Add soups, pimento, green chilies and chicken.
Cover bottom of casserole with torn soft tortillas.
Add soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: On stove cook in large saucepan the tomatoes and tomato paste. Saute celery and onions in separate skillet.
When celery and onions begin to get tender, add to tomato mixture.
Brown ground beef in skillet, drain and add to tomato sauce.
Add seasonings to taste.
Cook slowly and stir often.
Prepare spaghetti noodles separately.
Serve sauce over noodles and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil the squash in salt water to which the minced garlic has been added.
When tender, drain well.
Thicken the tomatoes with the cornstarch and add the butter and minced onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Brown the ground beef in a skillet; add a little salt and pepper.
In a greased casserole, put a layer of squash, beef, tomatoes and cheese; then repeat in the same order.
Cover the top with the crushed corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: easter ham loaf
directions: Mix well together pork, ham, one well beaten egg, breadcrumbs and milk.
Press evenly into a 10 x 10-inch casserole or cake pan. Bake for one hour in 350° oven, uncovered.
Remove from oven, pour off juices and brown pineapple slices in juice in a frying pan.
While pineapple is browning, mix together brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard.
Pour this syrup over ham loaf and return to oven at 350° for at least 15 minutes.
Arrange pineapple slices over loaf before serving.

title: italian cream liqueur
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or food processor fitted with a steel blade.
Process briefly until completely blended. Pour into bottles or airtight container and refrigerate.
Serve chilled.
Yields about 2 1/2 pints of liqueur.

title: praline biscuits
directions: Place 2 teaspoons margarine, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch. Sprinkle cinnamon in each cup.
Heat in oven until melted.
Mix Bisquick, applesauce and milk until dough forms.
Beat 20 strokes. Spoon onto mixture in cups.
Bake about 10 minutes at 450°.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast together.
Mix flour, sugar, margarine and egg together.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in airtight bowl and seal.
Place in refrigerator.
Dough is best if allowed to stand overnight.
Grease muffin tins, spoon out as needed.
This dough does not have to sit out before baking.
Will keep for 6 days in refrigerator.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jello salad in a jiffy
directions: Mix dry jello and cottage cheese, then add pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip.
It's done and ready to serve!
Sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.

title: shrimply cauliflower
directions: Combine cauliflower with a small amount of water in a glass dish.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes or until tender; drain.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Combine milk, onion and dill in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and strain; keep warm.
Blend flour and margarine in a saucepan. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes, or until smooth but not brown.
Stir in warm milk gradually.
Cook over low heat until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and white pepper. Stir in shrimp.
Spoon over cauliflower; top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Parboil beans until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ableskiver(swedish shaped pancakes)
directions: Combine mix, eggs, butter and half and half.
Beat until smooth.
Heat Ableskiver pan over moderate heat until drop of water bounces or use muffin pan.

title: heavenly pineapple pie
directions: Whip the cream in small bowl.
Refrigerate.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Beat together cream cheese, reserved juice and pudding in medium bowl until smooth.
Gently fold pineapple and whipped cream into pudding mix.
Spoon into pie crust.
Place in freezer until hard, 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Sprinkle top with more crumbs.
Serves 8.

title: cream puffs
directions: Place water and margarine in a saucepan; bring to a boil. When margarine is melted, add the flour while saucepan is still on the stove.
Stir with a fork until dough forms a ball around the fork, then remove from heat.
This takes only a minute.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Do not underbeat.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 425° oven, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 20 minutes.
Turn off heat and open door, but do not remove puffs from oven until they are cool.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix the first four ingredients with 1/4 cup flour.
Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together 1 3/4 cups flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in candy mixture by hand.
Drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 325°.

title: aunt jan's southern style ham
directions: Remove rind from ham.
Rub fat with cinnamon, ginger, allspice and nutmeg.
Prepare the pastry.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend in shortening.
Add water to make dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Place rolled dough around ham, joining at the bottom or side.
Cover pastry with well-greased and floured paper. Bake in slow oven at 300° for about 6 hours.
At the end of the fourth hour, remove paper to brown the dough.

title: sour cream and apple coleslaw
directions: Mix sour cream and egg yolks in medium bowl.
Add lemon juice, horseradish, paprika, sugar and salt; mix well.
In large bowl, mix shredded cabbage and apple.
Pour dressing over all; toss until well coated.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: red pudding(rodgrot)
directions: In a large saucepan, place berries and water and cook for 5 minutes.
Strain through a sieve; there should be about 4 1/2 cups of juice.
Mix the cornstarch and sugar and add enough water to make a thin paste.
Return the juice to the pan and again bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in cornstarch mixture.
Bring quickly back to a boil for 2 minutes and then remove from the heat.
Cool somewhat.
Pour carefully into a large glass bowl or individual glass dishes.
Sprinkle a little sugar on the top to prevent a skin from forming.
Best made several hours to a day ahead.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: ernie's goulash
directions: Let simmer, uncovered, 15 or 20 minutes.

title: mini fruitcake
directions: Cut fruit; mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 11 to 12 dozen.
Buy mini cupcake cups.

title: marinated and grilled shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in a shallow dish and mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain shrimp, reserving marinade.
Place shrimp in 6 (14-inch) skewers.
Grill over medium-hot coals for 3 to 4 minutes per each side, basting frequently with marinade.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Cut steak into strips; brown in small amount of oil.
Slice raw vegetables according to family size; pour over meat.

title: aunt georgie's scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 7 minutes; save 3/4 cup water.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour, water and milk.
In buttered casserole, put layer of cabbage, layer white sauce, 1/2 of cheese; repeat.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine with 1/2 cup bread crumbs; top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, onion, sour cream, cheese and almonds.
Mix together and turn into a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan.
Crumble crackers into margarine. Spread cracker mixture over top of casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: romano cheese salad dressing
directions: Blend well together and coat each serving with dressing, then sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: deep-fried zucchini
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine 1 cup flour, cornstarch, baking powder, salt, lemon pepper, onion powder, milk and egg.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch diagonal slices.
Rinse and pat dry.
Shake slices in remaining 1/2 cup flour to coat.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Mix all up and put into jar and shake real well.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and water on medium speed until thoroughly mixed.
Pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave creamy beef-cheese dip
directions: Place unwrapped block of cream cheese in a 1-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High 45 seconds to 1 minute or until cheese is softened. Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Cover and microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir. Microwave on Medium an additional 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Serve with chips, toast rounds or crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Make Jell-O and let stand until a little thick.
Let cake cool; poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour Jell-O over cake so it runs into the holes.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip together and ice cake with mixture.

title: achiote
directions: Adobo is simply a mix of black peppercorns, oregano and garlic. Sprinkle the meat with ground pepper, garlic powder, dried oregano and sometimes onion powder.
Then marinate it in olive oil and vinegar.
Others prefer fresh lime juice to the vinegar.
If you adhere to strict standards, then a basic Adobo mix would be:

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Mix crabmeat, cheese, onions and pimento in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into plate; bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: bacon, tomato and herb dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir together ingredients until well blended.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare 6 muffin cups or one 10-inch cast-iron or other heavy ovenproof pan.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir pepper and cheese into the dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, whisk wet ingredients together.
Mix dry and wet ingredients together and pour into prepared pan or muffin cups. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes half a dozen muffins or one 10-inch skillet.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: tuna crunch salad
directions: Combine tuna and water chestnuts in a medium-size bowl; stir in lemon juice, then mayonnaise or salad dressing and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If too dry, add more mayo and vinegar. I garnish with spanish olives.
Chill and serve.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, add all seasonings. Reserve 1/2 tablespoon of seasonings.
Sprinkle majority of seasonings on chicken.
Add the 1/2 tablespoon of seasonings to flour and corn meal.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk, mustard and white wine.
Dip the chicken in this mixture, then dredge in flour and corn meal.
Spray pan with vegetable spray, then spray chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: italian beef au jus
directions: Place beef roast in slow cooker; combine sauce ingredients and pour over beef.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.
Meat may be sliced and served with hard rolls; or shredded and served over rice or noodles.
Thicken broth with flour.

title: baked ziti casserole
directions: Cook pasta as directed, drain. Brown ground beef and flavor with garlic and onion powder.
Mix pasta, beef and spaghetti sauce.
Put 1/2 of mixture in large casserole, put 1/2 of cheese on top. Finish with rest of pasta mixture and top with rest of the cheese.

title: mayonnaise spice cake
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and honey.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternating with water.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease baking pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2-inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
This makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, self-rising flour and cocoa well.
In a saucepan, pour milk and add egg yolk.
Gradually stir in sugar mixture and mix well.
Cook on medium heat until thick (about 20 minutes).
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust. Top with meringue and brown in oven at 325°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sprinkle sugar substitute over bananas and stir; blend in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add walnuts. Blend thoroughly into banana mixture.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.

title: french market soup(southern living magazine)
directions: Sort and wash soup mix; place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above soup mix; let soak 8 hours.
To speed soaking time: boil 2 quarts water; add bean mixture and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Drain and proceed as directed.
Drain soup mix and return to pan; add 2 quarts water and ham hock.
Bring to boil; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Remove ham hock; remove meat from bone.
Chop meat and return to soup.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: wheeling station pesto
directions: Puree pine nuts and garlic with olive oil in food processor. Add basil, spinach and pepper.
Process on puree for 2 minutes. Add cheeses and puree for 1 additional minute.
Serve over pasta for a very healthy and filling meal.

title: apple pecan pancakes
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Add apples and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar, salt and milk in a saucepan and cook to 235° or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cool, add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered pan and cool until set.

title: french breakfast puffs
