directions: Cream 1/2 cup sugar, egg and shortening.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fill 12 greased muffin pan holes 2/3 full with batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, dip puffs, while hot, in melted butter, then roll into 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture.
Freezes well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in the bottom of pan.
Mix the cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Soften cream cheese and oleo. Add confectioners sugar and mix with mixer.
Pour over cake and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Leave in pan if too sticky to invert.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix bran cereal with boiling water, stirring to moisten evenly. Set aside to cool. Add eggs, buttermilk, oil and fruit.
Blend well. Stir together soda, salt, sugar and flour. Add to bran mixture. Bake now or refrigerate in a tightly covered container for up to two weeks.
Spoon batter into muffin cups 2/3 to 3/4 full. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: fantasy fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave margarine in microwave dish on High for 1 minute, or until melted.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave mixture on High for 5 minutes, or until mixture begins to boil.
Stir after 3 minutes; mix well.
Continue to microwave 5 1/2 minutes more, again stirring at 3 minutes.
Add chips, stirring until melted. Add Fluff, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.

title: dutch pumpkin nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, blend pumpkin, water, egg, cinnamon and mace. Add bread mix and stir until moistened.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan and cool.
If desired, frost with confectioners sugar.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: In a large skillet, crumble together the beef and sausage. Cook over medium heat, stirring until meat is browned.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is limp.
Drain off fat.
Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with half the chilies; top with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Add meat mixture and top with remaining chilies; set aside.
Beat together eggs and flour until smooth; add milk, salt and Tabasco.
Blend well.
Pour egg mixture over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
In a large pot add beans, seasoning mix, chili powder and canned tomatoes together. Add ground beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Shell, rinse and split eggs.
Place whites on a tray.
Set aside. In large bowl, mix yolks, onion, pickles, juice, mustard and mayonnaise.
(If mixture is too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.) Add salt and pepper.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: cream cheese dainties(sugary or sugar-free)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the butter and cream cheese until well blended.
Mix in flour.
Divide dough into 4 sections.
Cover and refrigerate until easy to handle.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Combine eggs, milk and onion.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls into hot, deep oil at 360° and fry about 2 minutes, turning over once or twice until golden.
Drain on paper towels.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all but raisins, then blend in raisins.
Use greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 1 hour more.

title: quick egg drop soup
directions: Bring soup to a boil.
Sprinkle pasta in slowly, so that boiling does not stop.
Cook until tender.
Reduce heat below boiling point.
Drop beaten egg in by teaspoons, stirring constantly.
Do not return to a boil after adding egg.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine cornbread, onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth; mash and mix with potato masher.
Add egg and mix well.
Bake in a roasting pan at 450° for 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine flour, eggs, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt and enough buttermilk to make it the consistency you prefer.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Best if made the night before you need it.

title: teresa's cinnamon raisin popcorn
directions: In greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, place popcorn and raisins. In 2-quart saucepan, stir together remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil for 5 minutes.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Do not mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Place cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg in a large mixing bowl. Beat with electric mixer until slightly blended. Beat in remaining eggs, one at
a time. Beat until lumps are gone. Pour over graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean, about 40 minutes. Yields 20 servings.

title: holiday fruit bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat oleo and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix bran cereal, milk and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients with cherries, nuts and dates; mix well. Spread batter into two greased 9 x 9-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: cheese log
directions: Toast almonds at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Chop 1/4 cup of the almonds and set aside.
Grind together 1 cup almonds, cheese (Cheddar) and cream cheese.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion and salt.
Blend thoroughly and shape into log about 8 inches long by 2 inches in diameter.
Roll in 1/4 cup chopped almonds.
Wrap in moisture-proof wrap.
Chill overnight and slice to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar together until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix thoroughly after each one.
Add water and pumpkin until blended and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Add dry mixture into pumpkin mixture, a little at a time; blend thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chili's cheese cake
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted butter or margarine.
Mix and press hard in bottom of two 9-inch pans.
Put in freezer for a while until cheese mixture is poured into them.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Combine corn and other ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake for 1 hour. Serve hot with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix in large pot the tomato sauce, tomato paste, 2 1/2 to 3 cans water (15 ounces), onion, 1 tablespoon sugar, 15 to 20 shakes Italian seasoning, 25 shakes sweet basil, 3 to 4 chunks bell pepper.
Sprinkle garlic powder to cover lightly.
Cook on medium to high until boiling.
Turn to low, stirring occasionally.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups of water slowly for 20 minutes.
When done, add 1 cup water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend in 1 cup shortening.
Mix with raisins.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: jello delight
directions: Drain fruit juice into 2 cup measuring cup and add milk to make 2 cups.
Add Jell-O and mix well, then add fruit and refrigerate.
Very low in fat.
I use this for a quick dessert when I need one fast.

title: one bowl rocky road brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl at High (2 minutes) or until completely melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in sugar; mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and 1 cup nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle marshmallows, chips and remaining nuts over brownies.

title: jane's cranberry chutney
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and place in saucepan.
Add sugar, cranberries, raisins and spices.
Heat to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add nuts and pineapple. Excellent served with ham, turkey and chicken.
Keeps well in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate cinnamon buns
directions: In mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add shortening, salt, sugar, egg, cocoa and 1 cup flour. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed of mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl. Stir in remaining flour. Blend well. Scrape sides of bowl. Cover with cloth. Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour. (If kitchen is cool, place dough on rack over bowl of hot water. Cover completely with towel.) Stir down by beating 25 strokes. Turn soft dough on well floured cloth-covered board. Roll into rectangle, 12 x 9-inch. Spread with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture. Roll up, beginning at wide side. Pinch edge into roll. Cut 12 pieces. Place on greased 9-inch square pan. Let rise in warm place until double, about 40 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Fill gallon container with the ingredients.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix the ingredients; pour into 1 to 1 1/2 gallon ice cream mixer and freeze.
Taste like Wendy's Frosty.

title: chocolate cookie cheesecake(preparation time: 38 minutes)
directions: Combine ingredients in a medium bowl; firmly press mixture in bottom and 2 inches up sides of a lightly greased 10 inch spring form pan.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Set aside.

title: apple bread
directions: Chop apples and cover with sugar.
Add oil and egg.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter. Remove from heat.
Pour over cornflakes.
Mix and spread on buttered cookie sheets.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add to Cool Whip.
Stir dry peach jello in Cool Whip and chill.

title: john bigotti (honest john)(casserole)
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat, add pepper, onion, mushroom soup and cheese; cook together.
Add noodles and tomato soup.
Pour into baking dish, cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fancy cookies
directions: Add pecans or chocolate chips to other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful 1-inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Moisten spatula and remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: buttermilk pie no. 2
directions: To mix, add sugar and flour to butter and blend.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and buttermilk and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cornish hens with pear or apricot preserves
directions: Fill each hen with 1/4 cup grapes which have been tossed lightly into sugar.
Brush each hen generously with hot mixture of melted butter, preserves, salt and pepper.

title: jabchai(chop suey)
directions: Put noodles into boiling water of more than 180° and cook 5 to 6 minutes.
Rinse noodles with cold water and drain 2 or 3 times. Stir-fry sliced meats and vegetables.
Flavor the rinsed noodles with such various spices as sesame oil, sesame powder, soy sauce and sugar.
Add vegetables and meat.

title: skinny spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with chips of your choice (bagel, tortilla or crackers).

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and heat until melted.
Flour and brown chicken.
Place in baking dish and pour sauce over chicken and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice (if desired).
For large groups, use chicken wings.

title: peanut rounders
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts in a heavy saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it reaches soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and food coloring. Beat until mixture is creamy. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes 25 to 30 patties.

title: tarheel chocolate pie
directions: Melt together the butter and cocoa; add sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, milk, salt and nuts.
Mix well and pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: latin coleslaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing. Toss all and chill.

title: jan hagel
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk. Beat until light.
Add flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread evenly on a greased jelly roll pan (2 x 15 x 1-inch).
Brush on egg white. Sprinkle chopped nuts and sugar on mixture.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes until light brown.
Cut while warm.

title: spicy quesadillas
directions: In small bowl, combine tomatoes, taco sauce, 3 tablespoons onions, lemon juice and peppers.
Combine cheese with remaining onions.
For each quesadilla, sprinkle about 1/2 cup cheese mixture over it.
Spoon 2 tablespoons sauce over cheese.
Top with another tortilla, pressing gently.
Fry in skillet in small amount of hot oil until golden and cheese has melted, turning once.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with quesadillas for dipping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and scoop out all seeds. Combine the hamburg, rice, onion, salt and pepper, oregano, whole tomatoes and 1/2 can tomato paste.
Mix well and fill squash with this mixture.
To remainder of stuffing, add the tomato juice (reserved), 1/2 can tomato paste and water to make very soupy. Extra rice may also be added.
Put pan in a 350° oven; cover and bake until squash is tender, approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: oreo icebox cookies
directions: Put crumbled Oreos in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream
Crisco
and
sugar.
Add vanilla, salt and nuts. Gradually
add
flour. Roll into balls. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°. Roll in powdered sugar when hot, then again when cool.

title: eggplant quiche
directions: Partially bake crusts in preheated 450° oven for 6 minutes. Cook eggplant covered in boiling, salted water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain well.
Cook onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, soup, salt, sugar, oregano and black pepper.
Heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir into beaten eggs.
Fold in tomato, cheese and eggplant.
Pour into pie shells; top with Parmesan cheese (sprinkle on top).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot onion dip
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian style pork chops, rice and savory green beans
directions: Several hours before cooking, wash and season pork chops well. Cover and refrigerate about an hour.

title: special chicken breast
directions: In shallow baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), arrange single layer of beef.
Top with chicken.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Pour over all. Top with bacon. Cover and bake 3 hours at 250°. Then bake uncovered for 1 additional hour.

title: fried tomato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Now add just enough bread crumbs to make it stiff enough to drop ty tablespoonful into hot oil in frying pan.
Brown on both sides. Serve hot.
Makes about 10 or 12 cakes.

title: mauntaine cookies
directions: Put butter, brown sugar, eggs, baking soda, flour, nuts and raisins in bowl; mix and put on cookie sheet with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla and pineapple and beat again. Add food coloring and 7-Up cola and beat.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Transfer to large bowl; cool slightly.
Combine dressing, soy sauce and sugar.
Stir in warm rice.
Cover and chill.
Fold in remaining ingredients before serving.

title: great american potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, mustard, salt, pepper and celery seed; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, celery, sweet pickles and onion; mix lightly, then chill.

title: simmered smoked links
directions: Place sausages in slow cooker.
Combine brown sugar, ketchup and horseradish and pour over sausages.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours. Serve with toothpicks.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer, ham, then cheese over broccoli.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Bring milk, butter, sugar and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or foil until cooled.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain juice and remove bones from salmon.
Break up salmon in bowl.
Add bread crumbs and milk; mix well.
Distribute butter bits throughout.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, combine rice, and 2 tbsp. butter. Cook until rice is brown, stirring frequently. Slowly stir in 2 c. water, seasoning mix, and
canned tomatoes, bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cook on low 15 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Layer pork chops in casserole dish.
Peel potatoes; slice in half, layer on chops.
Slice onion.
Lay around over potatoes. Pour tomato soup on top.
Cover with foil.
Cook 1 hour in 400° oven.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all together.
Freeze (in plastic garbage bag).
When ready to use, take out of freezer 4 to 5 hours before using; let thaw partially.
Place in punch bowl and chip up with large fork. Then put ginger ale over punch.
Will be icy.
Serves approximately 25 people.

title: cheesy broccoli surprise
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add broccoli, ham, milk and cheese. Cook over low heat until thick and creamy.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice; mix hamburger and rice.
Cut top off green peppers. Stuff rice and ground beef in peppers.
Pour tomato sauce over peppers and bake.
Stuffs about 6 green peppers.

title: nut fudge
directions: Combine everything but nuts in double boiler. Stir until smooth.
Pour in nuts. Spread candy in buttered pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: kountry doughnuts
directions: Cut off crusts 'n feed to chickens...make sandwitches wid the jelly..cut enyway you lak.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring once.
Mix mayonnaise, bacon, eggs, onions, salt and pepper in large bowl. Add potatoes; mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: school rolls
directions: In
mixer combine 1/2 cup yeast and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well with
hand.
Then add 1 quart warm water or 1 cup butter or 1 cup vegetable oil.
Let rise until yeast works well.

title: chili relleno bake
directions: In a skillet, brown together the meat, onion and garlic. Grease an 8 inch or 9 inch square baking pan.
Place one can of chilies on the bottom of the dish.
Top with 1-1/2 c. cheese.
Add meat mixture and top with second can of chilies.
Beat together the eggs and flour.
Add milk and seasonings and pour over the meat mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: orange spinach salad
directions: Drain oranges; wash spinach and pat dry.
Combine all ingredients; add dressing and serve.

title: emma janes southern casserole
directions: Brown onions and meat in butter.
Cook noodles until just tender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Garnish with olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled cheeseburgers
directions: Cook desired number of hamburgers and grilled cheese sandwiches.
Before putting the 2 pieces of bread together, add a hamburger patty and your favorite condiment (ketchup, mustard, onion, pickle, etc.).
Delicious!

title: pancit canton(sauteed noodles, canton style)
directions: Slice chicken breast thinly; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of cornstarch and patis. Mix to coat chicken slices evenly and set aside.
Drain mushrooms.
Discard tough stems and slice thinly.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine the remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs, stirring well.
Spoon mixture over chicken; top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: hot bean dip
directions: In a large saucepan, combine refried beans, picante sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with sour cream and serve with tortilla chips. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the apples, sugar and nuts.
Let stand an hour, stirring occasionally so the mixture makes its own juice.
Add dry ingredients to apple mixture.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Stir by hand.
Pour batter into a greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Sift first four ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening until size of small peas.
Stir in egg; add milk, tablespoon at a time, until roughly forms into soft dough.
Form into 1-inch balls. Wet balls in beaten egg, then roll in sesame seed.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls a little.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet pickles from dills
directions: Drain juices off dill pickles and pour boiling water over and let cool.
Cut length wise and cover with the following syrup: Boil sugar, water and vinegar.
Pour over split pickles. Refrigerate for 3 or 4 days.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Heat some oil in
a cast-iron skillet.
Cut tomatoes in thick slices.
Dip in bread
crumbs,
then
in
beaten egg and milk, then back in crumbs
again.
Fry until tender and golden brown, topping with cheese during last few minutes of cooking.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet and drain off fat; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread on split semi-hard rolls or buns.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Saute the ground beef and onion in the fat.
Add the tomato sauce, water, rice, salt, pepper, sugar and flour.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Clean peppers; boil for 2 minutes and drain.
Stuff the peppers with hamburger mixture.
On top, add 4 tablespoons buttered bread crumbs and 4 tablespoons grated cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: josephine's recipe for out of this world pie
directions: Measure sugar and cornstarch into saucepan; mix well.
Add pineapple with its juice; mix well so no lumps form.
Stir in pie filling and food color.
Use a wooden spoon; stir gently to avoid mashing the cherries.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is well thickened, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in dry gelatin.
Let cool.

title: bully pudding
directions: Put all ingredients into a buttered baking dish; stir well and bake 1 hour in a moderate oven.
Serve with cream.
It is not necessary to cream the sugar and butter for the cake.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Allow vinegar and milk to clabber while mixing remaining ingredients (except soda) in order.
When ingredients are well blended, dissolve soda in clabbered milk. Stir into flour mixture.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool in pan on wire rack before cutting.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Stir sherbet and orange sections into jello and chill thoroughly.

title: asparagus with mock hollandaise sauce
directions: Place asparagus and water in a 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave dish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Turn back one corner to vent.
Cook on High for 7 to 9 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Let stand, covered, while cooking sauce.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook beef, onion and shortening in hot skillet.
Stir with fork until meat has lost its redness.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms, seasonings and Worcestershire sauce. Cover skillet.
Lower heat and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: rice casserole
directions: Grease pan.
Put in oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Layer bacon and cheese in pan.
Beat together the milk, mayonnaise, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pan.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: chicken and sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix together diced chicken, soup, sour cream, chilies and flavor in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Fry tortillas in oil
until flexible.
Place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls chicken mixture on each tortilla.
Place in casserole.
Top with cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Melt margarine. Add flour and milk. Thicken to make sauce. Add cheese to create cheese sauce.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan in the order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn dog munchies
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix according to directions except with milk instead of water. Pour batter into mini-muffin pan with 24 cups. Fill to 3/4 full. Cut each wiener into 4 bite size pieces. Place one piece in each filled muffin cup. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef in frypan.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Add tomato soup and simmer 5 minutes.
In second pan, cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Add 1 cup chopped onion and cottage cheese.
Layer alternately in casserole dish beginning with noodle mixture and ending with meat mixture (about 2 layers of each).
Top with grated cheese and bake in a 350° oven until onion is tender and cheese is melted. Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: ham bone soup
directions: Soak and cook beans according to instructions on package. Saute onion, ham and garlic.
Combine all ingredients, except the sherry, into a 6-quart pot.
Simmer 4 hours.
Add sherry just before serving.
Serves 8 to 10 generous servings.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix until smooth and pour over first layer.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour. Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: chocolate delight cheese cake
directions: Cut in together flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let crust cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together and spread onto cooled crust.
Mix milk and both packages of pudding together and spread onto cheese mixture.
Cool 6 to 8 hours.
Top with Cool Whip (optional).
Serves 10.

title: cheese sheet cake
directions: Roll out 1 package of crescent rolls to fit bottom of 9 x 13-inch or 13 1/4 x 9 1/4 x 5/8-inch pan.
Beat until creamy the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spread on top layer; roll out other crescent rolls.
Put over cream cheese.
Melt butter and spread on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas mexicana
directions: Brown sausage; drain and crumble.
Saute onion and garlic with sausage.
Add black-eyed peas, tomatoes, water, chili powder and salt.
Simmer for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Place ingredients in a 1-gallon plastic bag and shake well. Let it set for 24 hours.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend cottage cheese and yogurt in blender to remove all curds. Add skim milk to thin if necessary.
Blend in coconut extract. Combine mixture with drained fruits.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms, reserving a few slices.
Saute for a few more minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels.
Mix
pretzels with butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press into
a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes. Remove from oven and cool.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350° and lightly grease a 9 x 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: butter thin cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour together until it forms little beads.
Add cream and yolks.
Mix very well.
Roll out on floured board as thin as desired.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Dip in unbeaten egg whites; sprinkle with mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Place a few chopped nuts on top (optional).
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: poppy seed, almond bread
directions: Mix together sugar, vanilla, almond flavoring, oil and milk. Add eggs and poppy seeds.
Blend in flour, salt and baking powder. For 1 loaf, bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
For 6 mini-loaves, bake 35 minutes at 350°.
For 12 muffins, bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and glaze with confectioners sugar, milk and vanilla or almond extract.

title: cranberry nut mold
directions: Make jello as directed.
Add can of cranberries.
Allow to chill and set slightly.
Add balance of ingredients and mix well. Pour into mold and let set.

title: dill-lightful sour cream dip
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, dill weed and salt.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Yields 2 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put 1 tablespoon of butter and salt into water and bring to boil.
Add macaroni.
Use just amount of water that when macaroni is done, it won't have to be drained.
Watch closely.
Add 1/4 of the cheese to macaroni quickly.
Mix well until cheese melts. Melt butter; add to milk and stir into macaroni so it won't be dry.
(Add more milk, if needed.)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and poke rest of cheese cubes into macaroni.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until it bubbles.

title: rolled biscuits
directions: (If using self-rising flour, omit salt and baking powder.)

title: pizza beef casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients well; do not brown meat. Spread meat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with tomato sauce.
Place Mozzarella cheese on top.
Top with oregano, basil, seasoned salt and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 60 minutes.
Nice served with tossed salad and Italian bread.

title: currant jelly fondue
directions: Heat jelly and mustard together to boiling point. Put in fondue dish and keep hot. Provide skewers for people to dip the bread cubes into the fondue.

title: pear bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate dry ingredients with liquid.
Bake in greased pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken easy(servings 6 to 8)
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients as listed.
Dribble melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar pie
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugars and milks in blender; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle top of pie with cinnamon and dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then at 350° until center is set, about 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and bell peppers into thin slices and sprinkle with salt.
Add 1 quart of cracked ice.
Cover for 3 hours.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven. Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper; coat chicken. Bake 35 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Bake 15 minutes or until done.

title: lagniappe red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans twice.
Place in at least 4-quart heavy pot.
Add water, ham and sausage.
Place on medium heat.
While beans are soaking and warming, chop onions.
Add to pot.
When the mixture boils, reduce and cover.
Stir every 20 to 30 minutes for 3 hours. Then, with a wooden spoon mash about 1/4 of the beans against the side of the pot.
Forty minutes after mashing beans, add cayenne pepper (not too much).
Cook 30 minutes more while cooking rice. Serve over rice.
Vegetables cook away to nothing.
The mashed beans thicken sauce.
Even better the next day.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken.
Add water and cover.
Simmer.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine brown sugar and cornstarch. Add pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add pineapple, green peppers and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: nana's chili soup
directions: In pan, fry hamburger; set aside.
Peel potatoes, cut into small pieces and boil with macaroni.
(When it is finished boiling do not drain water.)
Add onion, chili, stewed tomatoes, salt to taste and chili powder to taste, then add fried hamburger.
The longer you let it simmer the better, at least 30 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Goes really good with Nana's cornbread.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Simmer all ingredients together for 1/2 hour.
Layer in casserole dish with shredded Mozzarella cheese and cooked bacon (any amount).
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 15 minutes.

title: chalupas
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan and cover with water.
Cook, covered, over low heat.
Add water as needed.
After approximately 6 hours, take bones out of meat and break meat up.
Then cook with lid off into thick mixture for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve over corn chips and add the following as desired:
grated cheese, chopped onion, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, diced avocados and hot salsa.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: fat-free fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Stir about 30 strokes, or until mixed well.
Chill about 1 hour before serving. Dip fresh fruit into fruit dip.

title: dianes delicious dip
directions: Mix and heat until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Blend 1/4 cup cracker crumbs with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oriental pork loin
directions: Mix marinade, marmalade, garlic, dry mustard and ground ginger in a bowl. Put pork tenderloins in gallon-sized Ziploc and pour marinade in bag and close. Marinate several hours; overnight is best.

title: scotchy peanut bars
directions: Cream butter. Add brown sugar and cream well. Blend in flour (mixture may be crumbly).
Press into bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Combine all
ingredients in food processor. Blend until well mixed. This is a very pungent dressing, but good on spinach salad. (Note: Don't expect anyone to kiss you after eating this dressing!)

title: tomato-mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Remove mushroom stems.
Place mushrooms, round side down, in a shallow baking dish.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Add remaining ingredients and mix as biscuits.
Pinch off dough, about the size of a walnut and roll out biscuits.
Let stand a few hours to rise. Bake in 425° to 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
May store dough in refrigerator in a sealed bowl and use as needed.
This will keep 4 or 5 days.

title: 8 dozen buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 Tbsp. sugar in 2/3 cup water.
In 2 quarts water, dissolve sugar, lard and salt.
Stir in egg, yeast mixture and 5 cups flour.
Mix well and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in a greased pan, and let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape and place on greased jellyroll pan.
Let rise until double and bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
OR... you can use this recipe to make cinnamon rolls.
You roll out the dough into a rectangle, spread with butter or margarine and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
If desired you can add walnuts or pecans.
Roll the dough up like a jellyroll and cut into 1 to 1 1/2 inch pieces.
Place into a pan and let rise until double and bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.
OR... you can make donuts by cutting circles and a hole in the middle, letting them rise till double and deep fat frying them.
Immediately dip in sugar or glaze after they have cooled a short time.
OR...you can take a piece about the size of a lemon and stretch it out and deep fat fry it and put butter and jelly on it.
They are better if you eat them right away while they are still hot.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix baking soda and water together.
Beat in eggs.
Dump in cake mix and pumpkin pie mix.
Beat all together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked zucchini with cheese(serves 3)
directions: Put the zucchini in a colander or on towels to drain off the moisture.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 2-quart casserole dish. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef fiesta
directions: Brown beef and drain. Mix all ingredients together except for potatoes. Put in a casserole dish. Spoon potatoes around top of casserole. Sprinkle a little chili powder on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until potatoes are slightly brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add flour and blend to a paste.
Stir in heated stock and cook, stirring until sauce is thickened.
Cool. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add sauce to chicken mixture; mix and chill.
Shape into croquettes.
Dip croquettes in milk or beaten egg; roll in bread crumbs.
Place croquettes in greased pan. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: walnut angel food cake
directions: Whip egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar and continue to whip until they hold a point and are not dry.
Add 1/2 cup sugar slowly, then the extract.
Add flour, remaining sugar and nuts.
Bake in an ungreased pan for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add to corn.
Add salt, pepper, flour, cream and butter.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: iced tea(flavored and no calories)
directions: Place tea bags in coffee filter of automatic coffee maker. Make tea as if making coffee.
While hot, add lemonade mix and Sweet 'N Low.
Place in a container and add two additional coffee pots of water (1 to 2 proportions).
This is very good to have on hand and I use decaffeinated tea bags.

title: rich chocolate pudding
directions: Melt butter in a small pan.
Set aside.
In a separate pan, warm milk.
Stir cocoa and boiling water together to make a paste, then mix in melted butter.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt and add to warm milk.
Add the cocoa-butter mixture and egg.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened, 15 to 20 minutes. Don't let mixture boil.
Remove from heat and mix in remaining butter and vanilla.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook frozen broccoli for 10 minutes; drain it.
Melt butter and mix to Ritz crackers that should be crushed; set aside.

In a large bowl, mix together onion, cream of celery soup, beaten eggs, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, salt and pepper, then add broccoli. Pour mixture into a greased casserole and top with moistened crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake uncovered.
When top is light brown, it's done.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of the butter and mix with egg, cocoa, vanilla, crumbs, coconut and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350°.

title: potato squares
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until fork-tender.
Cool.
Peel and grate.
Melt oleo over low heat.
Stir in cheese.
Add mixture to potatoes along with sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Turn into a greased, shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: sugar & spice cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, honey, milk and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put dough in refrigerator for 1/2 hour. Form in balls and flatten.	Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: sugarless banana bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and sugar together.
Scald with boiling water.
Add melted butter.
Beat eggs and add milk to eggs.
Put the 2 mixtures together.
Add baking powder.
Pour into baking pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes in oven at 350°.
